t before our human relationship\" . He goes on to say that he doesn\'t know how to spell the word, but he thinks that it\'s important because it refers to the functions of plants before their human relationship. He says that plants need the surrounding environment to do their work. The narrator describes the weather for the next few days and says that he loves the changing seasons. He leads a walk with his partner in the Eroosa River Valley. They had a great time. The weather was beautiful and the landscape was beautiful. He wanted to learn more about the plants, so he decided to read some more. He chose to read a book about plants called \"nature\'s garden\" by Samuel Thayer, and a book called \"The book of field and roadside\" by John Eastman. The first book is from Samuel Thayer. The description of the plant is that it is a species of aster. It has a rosette of leaves that looks like dandelion. The leaves have hairs on the midrib, which is different from the leaves of the other plant. It is also very thin, unlike the other plants. The stalk looks like someone forgot to shrink the leaves. The plant has sessile leaves, which are smaller than the leaves in the rosette. The flowers have ray florets, which means that each flower petal on the flower has its own flower, not the other way around. They open',NULL,'The Garden of Aster: A Plant That Looks Like a dandelion'),(61924,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/31/CFRU Playlist - July 31, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-31 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-08-16 03:00:50',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61925,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/07/Blues Around the Block - August 7, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-07 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-08-16 03:00:51',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61926,81,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/07/The Sentinel’s Marvellous Kaleidoscope - August 7, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-07 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-08-16 03:00:51',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61927,82,'https://arch