to get started with a music library (13 minute read)'),(65014,99,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/04/The Stillness & The Dancing - October 4, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-04 09:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-07 15:40:27',NULL,'The Stillness and the Dancing is an hour-long radio show hosted by the Canadian musician, singer, and curator, The Stillsman. The show begins with a heavy note, as the performer announces that he has been recently diagnosed with a rare, optimistically malignant form of breast cancer. He has had to withdraw from his studies for the semester and will be going to Toronto to get treatment. The doctors are hopeful that he will recover, but uncertainty is something he lives with in his world. He describes the outpouring of support he has received from his listeners and friends, and he hopes to continue his show for the eight year anniversary. He says that he is also concerned that his new programming will be inconsistent over the next few months, as he will be undergoing radiation treatments for the disease. He hopes that his show will continue to be well received, as it has done for him. He adds that the show is also a somber one, as there is a lot of music that he just loves',NULL,'The Stillsman’s radio show tells us why he has been diagnosed with breast cancer '),(65024,100,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/04/We Know Some Stuff + CFRU playlist - October 4, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-04 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-04 18:06:49',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(65025,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/04/Democracy Now - October 4, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-04 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-04 18:08:03',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(65028,155,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/2pu5yx/DrMouth_CIUTshow_oct3_2023_fullshow.mp3','2023-10-04 18:14:25',287930048,'2023-10-04 20:05:22',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(65036,1586,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/04/What Do You Do? - October 4, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','202