rate. Finally, they ask Julia to deliver her announcements for the party. Julia says that she\'ll pay to deliver them if she wants to. She says that if there\'s anything she\'d like to know about the accessible parking, she\'s willing to pay if she just wants to know what Paul has to say about it. She adds that she would like to follow up on that. She also says that the party will be a great way for people to connect with each other. The group thanks Julia for her report. They also thank Jess from Tennessee who was there to make sure everything was going well. They mention that they\'ve got two council meetings on the same day. The first is about housing and the second is about demolition',NULL,'The Ten-Kart Party: What\'s Next for Paul and Paul? (13 minute read)'),(66374,79,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/16/Breezy Breakfast Radio - October 16, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-16 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-09 05:16:33',NULL,'The gang at the 10 C\'s discuss how they\'re celebrating 15 years in business. They\'re also talking about the city\'s new land acknowledgement, which means that the city is acknowledging that the land that they call home is part of the territory belonging to the Credit First Nations. Julia Grady, co-founder of Tensee, is joining them. She\'s also excited to be here, because she\'s a member of the group and she\'ll be able to tell them all about Tensee. Tensee is a membership-based organization that\'s working to make the world a better place.',NULL,'The 10 C’s are celebrating 15 years in business – and they’re excited to join them '),(66375,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/17/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - October 17, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-17 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-17 16:06:10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66376,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/16/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - October 16, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-16 08:00:00',86638720,'2023-10-17 16:06:11',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66377,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/17/CFRU Playlist - October 17, 2023 at 06:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-17 06:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-17 16:06:11',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66378,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/16/CFRU Playlist - October 16, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-16 14:00:00',86638720,'2023-10-17 16:06:12',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66379,86,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/16/The Deep House Project - October 16, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-16 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-31 05:21:11',NULL,'On this week\'s Deep House Project, we hear about the release of Lauren\'s debut, The Lost Art Of Through. The album is full of pop, folk, and jazz elements. We also learn that the International Institute of Critical Studies and Improvisation will be holding its fourth annual Festival of Improvised Arts on October 20 and 21 at the university. The show starts off with the classic track So Glad by Legendary Fingers Incorporated. The song is about a young woman who has fallen in love with someone else. She tells the girl that she\'s too proud to love her because she doesn\'t know all that she knows about love. She says she\'ll never be the first person to break her heart, but she will never be first to say it. She\'s not just saying she loves her, she loves the girl she loves. She won\'t let it go like this. She wants her Pin Springs to stop loving her. The Underground Man plays some remixes of some of Tim Walsh\'s tracks. He closes the show with an \"AI sounding trackopia\" from him.',NULL,'Lauren\'s debut album, The Lost Art Of Through, is a big hit for the world'),(66380,87,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/16/Back in the USSR - October 16, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-16 23:00:00',86638720,'2023-10-17 16:06:16',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66381,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/16/Blues Around the Block - October 16, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-16 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-17 16:06:19',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66382,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/16/Blues Around the Block - October 16, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-16 19:00:00',86638720,'2023-10-17 16:06:19',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66383,85,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/16/Ripcord Radio - October 16, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-16 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-17 16:06:21',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66384,82,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/16/Big Sis Radio - October 16, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-16 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-17 16:06:22',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66385,83,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/16/to know the land - October 16, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-16 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-30 16:03:27',NULL,'On this episode of Know the Land: The Land, Byron speaks with his friend, artist, Miki Tamblyns about her recent project, called Animal Forms. The project is a mask making project that invites people to come to the forest to interact with the masks and have a sit spot. The masks represent different mammals living in the forest, and people are invited to record their impressions in journals and take photographs. The idea of seeing the world from another\'s point of view excites Byron, who is fascinated by the idea that humans can see the world as it is and see that their actions affect other people. He is inspired by Joanna Macy\'s work with the Council of Beings and also by the work of the artist. He was also interested in the idea of making masks to represent animals and then having people come together and share what is going on. He says that the world is alive, and that he wants to get into this because a lot of times he feels like he is like animus, which is a term that he has come to use in his life. He wants to know more about how people participate in this project, naming their own masks, and how they feel about the mirrors. He likes the mirrors because they allow people to look at themselves in a mirror, and he likes that the project is about inspiring and encouraging people to be more empathetic. He also likes the book she has been reading, Becoming Animal, by David Abrams, which he finds very helpful.',NULL,'How To Make a Mask To Be a Friend of Miki Tamblyns'),(66386,81,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/16/The Sentinel’s Marvellous Kaleidoscope - October 16, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-16 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-17 16:06:23',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66387,101,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/15/Seems Like Old Times - October 15, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-15 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-17 16:06:34',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66388,101,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/15/Seems Like Old Times - October 15, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-15 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-17 16:06:35',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66389,108,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/15/Wind-Down - October 15, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-15 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-17 16:06:37',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66390,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/16/Here Today - October 16, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-16 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-07 06:51:10',NULL,'The band is comprised of musicians from different bands. The first song they play is an EP called Harvest. It\'s a great song because they\'re getting close to Halloween. Then the band plays a new album called Transients and the song they cover is a cover of a Bernard Crowley song called Pet Sematary. The band also plays a song called Lampshade. They also play a song they just heard called John Fox and The Maths Destination. They play two songs from Hotel Myra\'s new album I am not Myself. The name of the band is changed to Hotel Myra, which reflects the dirty direction of the music. So now they\'ll move to Winnipeg for the new band called Apollo Suns and they play a Paul McCartney song called \"The Kiss of Venus\" from his latest album.',NULL,'Hotel Myra is a Canadian band based in Winnipeg, Manitoba. They\'ve been playing a lot of songs since they were'),(66391,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/15/Visions fugitives - October 15, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-15 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-17 16:07:11',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66392,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/15/Visions fugitives - October 15, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-15 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-17 16:07:13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66393,146,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/15/The Kookoo Bananas Variety Hour - October 15, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-15 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-08 15:04:55',NULL,'The guys decide to do an episode celebrating women, including women in music. We start with a song by a band called Bodega Run, which has a female vocalist. The song is called \"Crying\" and it\'s from their album \"Get Old.\" The guys like the song because it sounds like they\'re playing a game. They decide to have a song called \"When Brakes Get Ust,\" written by an amazing female singer named Mira Duaron. The guys think the song is a great one because it is about getting home from work in the rain and they all agree that it would be a bummer if they left their bike on the curb for a while. They also agree that if you left your bike on it for too long, it would rust and slip all over the place. They\'re also psyched that Jenny Omnicord will be singing her song \"An Amazing Woman We know\" in New York City. So that will be the first four songs in the show about women. But we\'ll also be hearing songs by other amazing women. The next song is by a super cool band called Uniq, who are made up of a bunch of female musicians. They play a song about two female musicians named Steff','It\'s International Women\'s Week this week if you\'re listening to us at the beginning of March. We thought we would do an episode that celebrates women, us three guys. We started with a song called Bodega Run by a group called Crying from their alb