m of international politics. He adds that the US is sending two aircraft carriers to the eastern Mediterranean to help with the situation in Gaza. He notes that the American leader\'s visit to Israel is part of a larger strategy to assert American power in the region. He argues that this strategy will help send a message to Israel that it can depend on the West. He further notes that this will challenge the unipolar nature of the international system of politics.\n\nThe point is that the international community will have to come up with a resolution to end the violence in Gaza because there is no end to the atrocities. Phil says that he noticed in the president\'s interview that he was very stressful. He said that the way that the New York Times',NULL,NULL),(66659,289,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/txqh9e/The_Next_Stop_121aj37v.mp3','2023-10-19 19:27:40',271912147,'2023-11-22 01:48:09',NULL,'The Next Stop is a music program hosted by Sage Ranaldo, a Canadian EDM composer. The program focuses on the work of composer and musician, Mort Garson.\n\nHe is a Canadian born and raised musician who studied music at the Juilliard School in New York. He was instrumental in the development of the Moog synthesizer and the Plantasia album. He also wrote music for the Apollo 11 moon landing, which took place on July 20, 1969. The program opens with a mix of tracks from the first two hours of the program. The first track is \"Zoos of the world\" from the late composer\'s second album Journey To The Moon And Beyond. The next two tracks are \"Captain DJ U Disco\" and \"Miharu Koshi\". The third track is called \"Lion Milk\" and the last is \"Mid-air Thief\".',NULL,NULL),(66660,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/19/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - October 19, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-19 08:00:00',86638720,'2023-10-20 04:06:17',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(66661,90,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/19/Bridging The Social Distance - October 19, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.