tarts off by talking about the releases from his favorite label, MGR and then moves on to some more obscure releases from other labels. He takes a moment to talk about his favorite, the album from His Tracks called Shortwave Nights and the album by his favorite project, Godspeed. This album is a bit of a departure from his usual horror music, but it\'s one of his favorites. The next track is Distraction and Loss of Desire from a band called Leisure Time Explosion. The track is one of the tracks from a new',NULL,'The Underground Man Listens to Some of His Favorite Releases '),(67344,99,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/25/The Stillness & The Dancing - October 25, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-25 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-07 14:43:46',NULL,'The Stillness and the Dancing begins with a spooky music track. The music is from Caixin, a Japanese label. The theme is \"a somewhat spectral theme\" . The release is called \"If only you knew what you claimed to\" and the music is by Richard Skelton, an artist who has spent much of his career creating ambient and lo-fi music.',NULL,'The Stillness and the Dancing (Sponsor), a new Japanese release by Richard Skelton '),(67346,155,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/y678iv/DrMouth_CIUTshow_oct24_fullshow.mp3','2023-10-25 17:23:52',287154368,'2023-11-18 10:13:41',NULL,'Dr. Mouse and his band get ready to head out for lunch, and Dr. Mice is psyched to be on board. He\'s impressed with how progressive and loud the band is. They\'ve heard a lot of prog from the past, and now they\'re psyched to hear some new stuff. They hear some of the latest music from a band called Nash the Slash, and they\'ll be playing some of their stuff at a Halloween party the next week.\n\nThis is cool, because this is the time of year when you\'re really into music. The band also plays some of James Brown\'s \"Funk Power,\" which is one of the most important songs in rock. They also play a song called \"Soul Motivators,\" which sounds like it was written by a guy named Bobby Bird.',NULL,NULL),(67354,195,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/g8rikh/Dementia13RadioShow_23_10_24.mp3','2023-10-25 15:41:01',287962512,'2023-11-18 10:01:45',NULL,'The show opens with a description of the character of the narrator, who is described as \"not a good girl\" . The narrator describes the girl as being a \"not-a-good\" person, who \"is not a good\" girl. He compares her to a girl who is not good, but not a bad girl.',NULL,NULL),(67356,100,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/25/We Know Some Stuff + CFRU playlist - October 25, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-25 12:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-18 09:50:22',NULL,'This is a short program of the music program on CFRU 93.2 FM. It\'s called \"We Know Some Stuff.\" This program is all about science and technology. It starts off with a little history lesson about how life on earth was very different than it is today. It was one time that civilization gave life to the world, and then it was destroyed. The program ends with a discussion about bread.\n\nThis is about how bread is a universal thing, and all different regions of the world have different bread. The bread from India is different from the bread from the West, and so on. The only difference is that it\'s more delicate. The whole thing is that the food industry works on people\'s preferences, so it makes sense that they\'re going to make the best bread possible.',NULL,NULL),(67357,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/25/Democracy Now - October 25, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-25 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-18 09:37:15',NULL,'The war in the Gaza Strip continues. The death toll is now 6,500, and the number of people displaced has reached 1.4 million, according to the United Nations. Israel\'s army chief has said it is ready for ground attack. The U-S has sent military officials to Washington.',NULL,NULL),(67360,158,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/gqubcb/radical_rev_11am_24th_oct7jtz1.mp3','2023-10-25 18:48:39',143961989,'2023-11-18 09:28:18',NULL,'The Radical Reverend hosts a conversation with Ren Jansen, president of the Ontario English Catholic teachers\' union, and Yvonne Runstetter, the union\'s assistant vice president. Ren tells the Radical Reverend that the government has wasted a year negotiating with the union. The union has been trying to get the government to come to the bargaining table with a renewed commitment to negotiate a fair deal for teachers. Ren adds that Minister Lecce is frequently asked about the state of the education system, and always says that the spending on education is higher than any other government in the world.',NULL,NULL),(67362,156,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/5k6fnb/pp_22nd7a1mn.mp3','2023-10-25 19:41:53',287962512,'2023-10-25 20:05:26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(67364,169,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/3h88r4/iw_23rd90xrb.mp3','2023-10-25 19:04:42',143961989,'2023-11-18 09:16:10',NULL,'On this edition of the show, Jenny Blackbird talks about some of the events she\'s been working on for the show. The show starts off with a song called \"Mi\'kmaq Song,\" which is based on a traditional Mi-kmaq song. This song is performed by a young Mi\'kmak man named Morgan Toney, and a dance is also performed by his mom, who is a teacher. Also, she has a young friend, Aluk, who has done a segment for the CBC Kids about a traditional dance.\n\nShe also talks about the upcoming week, called Indigenous Education Week, which will take place from October 30 to November 3. There will be workshops, lectures, and other events. If you are a student, staff, or faculty member at the University of Toronto, you can find out more about it on CLNX, the U of T\'s social media platform. There\'s also a traditional teaching with Jane Merrigal, who teaches from a Haudenosaune lens, on October 25th. There are also monthly fires at the house, which are open to the public.',NULL,NULL),(67370,209,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/iu2fw5/to_25th61ajo.mp3','2023-10-25 19:37:39',143961989,'2023-11-18 09:02:11',NULL,'This is the second part of a two-part interview with dance pioneer and founding curator of DanceWorks, Mimi Beck. The first part of the interview is devoted to describing her career, which has spanned more than 40 years. The second part is dedicated to describing the last time she and Nicole were on the same show, which was in 2019.',NULL,NULL),(67371,218,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/emf764/taylor_report_23rd781hk.mp3','2023-10-25 19:39:39',143961989,'2023-11-18 08:52:51',NULL,'The Taylor Report is hosted by Phil Taylor and consists of a series of short interviews with independent critics of the Bush administration. The first interview is about the recent demonstrations in the U.S. against the war in Syria. The second is about a demonstration in Toronto, organized by World Against War. The third is about how the Bush Administration is attempting to control the news. The fourth is about why they are trying to speak to David Mivis, a prominent Jewish rabbi in Canada, about the demonstrations in Washington.',NULL,NULL),(67372,217,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/pppvj9/CIUTOct24.mp3','2023-10-25 18:22:17',143961989,'2023-11-18 08:43:27',NULL,'This episode opens with a conversation between David Jaden, the proprietor of a popular dance hall, and a host of other music industry types. They discuss the various music acts that they perform each year for the Halloween season. The first of the two specials that David does each year is called \"The Late, Late lamented Transylvania.\" The other is \"Dead Bulls.\" They plan to continue the theme of \"The Bloodshot Bill\" with their \"Evil and Swing Breakers\" and \"Neck Breakers Adventures.\" They will also include \"The Coyote\'s Whale from the Dark Shoulder\" and a \"Voodoo trucker.\"',NULL,NULL),(67374,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/25/Volunteer Playlist - October 25, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-25 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-18 08:34:09',NUL