ality Assurance, where she has been asked to interview professors about implementing the International Education and Development Initiative. She is also looking forward to getting more interview experience as a campus outreach assistant.',NULL,NULL),(67778,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/28/Caribbean Anthology - October 28, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-28 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 18:37:08',NULL,'The next morning, the gang discusses the success of last night\'s party. They also discuss the cold weather that\'s been plaguing the area. The gang thanks the people who helped put on the party, including the organizer, Qaddaf, and the real estate agent, Discover Joy. Finally, they talk about how the recent pandemic has made it difficult for people to go to parties and other events.',NULL,NULL),(67779,35978,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/28/CFRU Live from 10C! - October 28, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-28 15:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 18:26:46',NULL,'This is the second part of a three-part interview with the Underground Man. The first part is a conversation between Underground Man and Underground Man\'s friend, the musician Laurie Anderson.\n\nAnderson and Anderson discuss the need for people to be more self-reflective, and Anderson suggests that this is the only way to get out of a jam. They also discuss the importance of listening to people around you and being able to see where they\'re coming from. They talk about how it\'s important to be able to be \"honest\" and listen to the needs of the moment. They discuss how the best thing to do is to be reflexive about the situation. They\'re also talking about how people need to be good at listening to their needs and the needs around them, and how to make the best of the situation they have.\n\nThe Underground Man is happy to hear this and he\'s happy to be part of this conversation. As part of the conversation, we hear from Chloe, a coffee roaster from Planet Bean. Chloe te