ctive of musicians, artists, and writers who live in Toronto. The interview is part one of a three-part series in which Dave tells his story. The first part of the interview takes place in a hotel room, where he describes the state of affairs in the building.\n\nThe second part takes place at the sound booth, where the musician and his friends listen to music. They begin with a song called \"I Feel Sanctified By the Commodores\" from a series of vinyl records, and the third part of this interview is a piece by Anne Pebbles called \"Can\'t Stand The Rain.\" The fourth part focuses on Maria Callis\'s performance of a piece called \"The Wall-E.\"',NULL,NULL),(67824,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/The Underground - October 29, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 13:44:50',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(67825,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/28/The Underground - October 28, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-28 23:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 14:02:38',NULL,' ',NULL,NULL),(67835,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/The Underground - October 29, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 13:30:15',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(67863,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Visions fugitives - October 29, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 13:22:39',NULL,'In this episode, the co-hosts explain that they are each choosing a piece of music to play each week. Each week, they will respond to the other\'s selections by choosing their own. For example, this week Fangwei will play a work by Morton Siotnik and another by Pablo Neruda called United Fruit Company.',NULL,NULL),(67873,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Visions fugitives - October 29, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 13:09:14',NULL,'The program opens with a discussion of Beethoven\'s Op. 17 , which is a cycle of nine dance movements. In this program, Christopher Curry responds to the recital with a piano concerto that he has selected for the week. The piano concerto he has chosen is not by Maurice Ravel, but rather by Eric Wolfgang , who lost an arm in the First World War. The piece, called the Piano Concerto for Left Hand, was written in 1922 for Paul Wittgenstein who lost his arm during the war, and was composed for the left-hand side of the piano. It is also written for Howard Shelley, who played it with the BBC Symphony Orchestra and conductor Matthias Spard.',NULL,NULL),(67874,146,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/The Kookoo Bananas Variety Hour - October 29, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-08 14:31:23',NULL,'The gang teases the audience by playing a short song called \"Scarecrow Songs.\" It\'s about Clementine, a song that\'s been sung by a guy named John Zacharels. Yeah, this guy is a big fan of Clementine, because she\'s a big favorite of his. But he\'s also got a new love in the making, a new crush named Clementine. The gang asks everyone in the house what their favorite candy is for Halloween. The oldest kid, Henry, says that his favorite is chocolate. The second oldest kid is Henry\'s friend, Rowan, who says that he likes snickers too much. The third kid is a teenager named Henry Jr. who says he likes chocolate too. The fourth kid is Jacky, who likes candy too.','This is our ninth Halloween special. We have so many songs so many scary songs to play. Let\'s go around the room and find out what everyone\'s favorite candy to receive on Halloween is. Rowan bought a padlock for his pillowcase. It\'s my last year I need to make the most of it.','Halloween Candy Picks (Sponsor - Part I)'),(67884,148,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Clan Na Gael - October 29, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 12:57:47',NULL,'This is a short program about the Clan Na Gael, a Scottish folk band. The program starts out with a song by Nonie Thompson, followed by a song from the movie Braveheart. It\'s a bit of a departure from the Clan\'s usual songs, but the music is still very good. The band closes out the program with another song from a collection of Scottish songs called Silver Collection. Marian Anderson\'s band also performs the song, but it\'s not as good as the first one.',NULL,NULL),(67894,101,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Seems Like Old Times - October 29, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 12:47:11',NULL,'The program starts off with a song recorded in 1941. It\'s called \"Seems Like Old Times\" and it\'s about Helen Forrest and her orchestra coming back to Europe.\n\nThe song is also called \"Down, Down, Down\" and is the title of this program. The program goes on and on about how much music and music history has changed over the years. Dick Hames is one of the greatest songwriters of all time, and he\'s coming to town with a tribute to his music. A Christmas Craft and Artisan Sale will be held in Guelph on Saturday from 10am to 3pm. It will be a unique event. It sounds like \"Holly\" from the Makebelieve Ballroom CD. We\'ll also be back on the air with \"Young at Heart\" from 1954.\n\nAnd then we\'re back to Frank Sinatra. He\'s singing Young at Heart on the program. And then he\'ll say hi to a couple of his listeners. Finally, the program closes with two more songs. The first is \"Bogie Woogie Bugle boy\" from Bette Midle and the second is \"Buddy Holly\" from Andrews sisters. And finally, \"Halloween is coming up\" and the program is going to scare you',NULL,NULL),(67895,148,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Clan Na Gael - October 29, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 12:35:05',NULL,'The show begins with a selection of songs from the Reel Time CD. The first song is Kelphic Thunder, a song by the Proclaimers. The second song is \"I\'m Going To Be 500 Miles\" , a Scottish song, and the third song is Rattlin. The band has disbanded, and they have put together an EP.\n\nThe fourth song is a song called \"Both Sides of The Tweed\" . The fifth song is the \"Fury Brothers and Arthur from Furys Finest,\" a song written by Eric Bogle . And the sixth song is The \"Greenfields of France,\" a version of the song that Bogle wrote. The seventh song is Rob\'s Pipe. The piper plays a piece from the Piper Legacy and D\'U A R T\'S Castle CD. He says that he plays some pipes. The next song is Maggie and Cassie from the Sterling Road CD. They sing about the \"King\'s Shilling,\" which sounds like it was written in Ireland and England, but in reality it\'s probably Scottish. The song starts off as a Celtic song, but then it changes its tune and sounds more like an English song. So the next song on the show',NULL,NULL),(67905,101,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Seems Like Old Times - October 29, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 12:23:15',NULL,'\"The Black Figurine of Death\" The Black Figurine \"of Death\" is a tale of fear, and this is the kind of fear that most of us will have in life. The narrator begins his story by explaining that he is afraid of death itself, and that he has experienced this fear firsthand.\n\nHe tells the story of the night his Uncle Amos died, when he held a small figurine in his hand. The figurine was dead, and no one was there to see it. He goes on to explain that all of the people of the Hall of Fame will want to know what it is like to be filled with fear, a fear that will last for the rest of their lives. He then tells them that they will wish they had never known him, that they would never be born before he died.\n\nHe says that they all will learn how to fear, like the pieces in a jigsaw puzzle, and they will learn to fear even more. Three days after his death, he is buried in the Johnson family land. Ten days later, the narrator reads his uncle\'s will. It divides the property equally among the three main sons.',NULL,NULL),(67906,149,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/La Buena Onda - October 29, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-29 22:07:15',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(67911,170,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/by837d/MUS-TU-4P_31_oct_-_2023-10-29_943_PMaojll.mp3','2023-10-30 01:48:59',111378520,'2023-11-17 12:08:27',NULL,'Ruby Slippers, the station manager, and program director, have given the hosts a second hour to perform some new music. The show begins with a brand new song from Alice and Cammy. The first song is from a duo called Mccarr, and the second is a song called Fancy Hercules.\n\nThe third song is Douglas Von Ervins Carnival from the Meet the Monsters. The fourth song is a message from a band called Ace Of Wands. The last song is one from CIUT, which is a well-known Halloween-kind of place. The band says that they\'re wishing everyone a happy Halloween. After this show, the hosts leave the listeners with some more songs from the Dolly Rot\'s.',NULL,NULL),(67917,200,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/g23gqj/karibuni_oct_28-236aisn.mp3','2023-10-30 01:59:56',287962512,'2023-11-17 11:57:37',NULL,'In this short conversation, we learn that the Bolshoi Theater is bringing a production of the opera \"From the Roots Up\" to Chicago. The Bolshoim\'s Artistic Director, Alexandre Dumas, has just won a prestigious prize at the Theater Club of Chicago for his artistic direction of the production. We also learn that Alexandre\'s wife, Nadine, recently won a major award at the same Theater Club. We learn from the Artistic Director that Alexandre intends to continue his work for at least another 100 years.',NULL,NULL),(67918,207,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/9vskru/Music_w_db_Hawkes_Nov_1_2023_podcast9tf2v.mp3','2023-10-30 12:00:05',281801664,'2023-11-17 11:43:50',NULL,'The next morning, kids want to eat chocolate-covered bars for breakfast, which is a big departure from their normal breakfast routine. The problem is that they\'ve got tons of candy. The trick is to slowly eat the candy down, so that it\'s gone down quickly.\n\nThe other option is to put the kids on a strict diet where they only get to eat a certain amount of food a day, and they can choose what they want. The third option, the one that makes sense to the author, is to let the kids gorge themselves on the candy, which will get rid of the sugar quickly. This way, the kids will learn to control their appetites later on.',NULL,NULL),(67919,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - October 30, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 08:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 11:33:24',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(67920,108,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Wind-Down - October 29, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 11:21:52',NULL,'This program is for you. It\'s called \"The Wind-Down\" and it\'s all about music. It starts off with a selection of spooky music and then we\'re introduced to October Country and my girlfriend is a witch.\n\nIf you want to know more about the music, check out the show\'s play-by-play page at the wind down. Here\'s what we learned today: \"The Shadow is also source of light / That produced that shadow.\" This is a reference to the song Crying Contest by the band Mother Tongues. And then we get a new song from Twin Temple called Let\'t Have a Satanic orgy. We then get a song from The Specials called Ghost Town. Then we get two songs from the Beach Loveitch called Sugar Land and October. The program ends with La Force by Exoskeleton.',NULL,NULL),(67921,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Here Today - October 30, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-07 05:59:50',NULL,'Aaron Badgley is back with his \"halloween\" show. He\'s going to kick it off with a song by Bing Crosby, \"I am a demon\" . Badgley explains that he\'s not a fan of trick-or-treating at all, but he\'ll do his best to entertain listeners. He tells listeners that he is a \"demon\" , a \"vampire\" and a \"wolfman\" ; that he sings songs about the supernatural . Finally, he explains that the song about the gums is actually a song about \"the gums\" and \"the g\" : \"The gums are called \'the gums\' . The g is called the gums, the g is the gums.',NULL,'Aaron Badgley\'s \"Halloween\" show kicks off with Bing Crosby song \"I am a de'),(67922,150,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Zombie Jamboree - October 29, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 19:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 11:11:18',NULL,'The UM takes over the program to discuss the upcoming Zombie Jamboree. He says that he\'s going to focus on the things that are important to him, such as how to survive in the dark. He also mentions that the first song he\'ll play tonight is from the special Bataclan concert. Next up will be \"The Wind Down.\"',NULL,NULL),(67923,150,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Zombie Jamboree - October 29, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 11:00:44',NULL,'This is the second part of the interview with Bruce, who introduces himself as \"your dungeon master\" and \"S-world in the next\" . This is part one of a two-part interview. The first part is about Bruce\'s role as a dungeon master and part two is about the music.\n\nThe music starts off with a song called \"MMIGW2s\" meaning \"Missing and Murdered Girls Women, and Two-spirited People\" , and it ends with \"It\'s Future Memories\". The music is a mix of songs, including two songs by Feller Kutu and two by Dave. The song \"Munich Central\" is also a song, and part one ends with the song \"Moth Yellow\".\n\nThe songs are all part of a service from the University of Guelph, which can be found on the university\'s website at www.curriculum.ca. The second part starts with Dave\'s explanation of his father\'s wolfman background, and then includes songs by Elizabeth, Sarah Through Chronoscope, Colliding Canyon, and the Yayaaz along with Dr Octagon. The Yayazes lead a \"Zombie Jamboree\" seminar, which is also part of this interview. It',NULL,NULL),(67924,149,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/La Buena Onda - October 29, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-30 14:07:39',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(67925,152,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Through the Looking Glass - October 29, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 10:50:05',NULL,'The show continues with a song from Woodhawk, followed by one from Well Bad and one from the Canadian artist Cammy Van- Houst. The first song is called \"My Alice featuring Barry\" and the second song is \"Am I Carrie\".',NULL,NULL),(67926,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/This Night Wounds Time - October 30, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 10:40:41',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(67927,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/This Night Wounds Time - October 30, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 10:34:54',NULL,'This chapter opens with the announcement that the band is going to play music from all over the world. The band has been going through different provinces of Buenos Aires for a while, and they\'ve been missing a show. So, they\'re back to the music. This time, though, it\'s Halloween. And, as always, the music will be a little different. Instead of playing music that\'s associated with the supernatural, it will be music from an Australian band called The Church.\n\nThe Church\'s first album, Sometime Any Place, came out in 1994. A lot of people think that this album and its follow-up, Among the Spirits, are the worst albums ever recorded by the band. But, according to the band, these albums aren\'t so bad. They\'re just not good enough. The first album is called Skins and Hearts, and it was recorded by a guy named Nick Ward. The second worst album is Seance, which was recorded in 1983, but it was also recorded with a production error that made the drums sound like \"pistol shots.\"',NULL,NULL),(67928,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/This Night Wounds Time - October 29, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 23:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 10:21:47',NULL,'This night, the band plays a psychedelic rock show. The band starts with a set from Vanishing Twin, followed by Chuck Copenas\'s \"Current,\" a track from \"Requisites,\" and then a track by Faith Healer. The show ends with an anticipatory song from The Church.',NULL,NULL),(67929,153,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Backtracks - October 29, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 10:10:43',NULL,'On this edition of CFRU 93.3, host Jennifer Eileen explains the history of Halloween. She tells listeners that it is a Celtic festival that marks the end of harvest and the start of winter. She explains that the festival of Samhain, also known as Samain, was believed to mark the beginning of the winter. The festival was celebrated with bonfires and animal skins. The name of the festival comes from All-Hath-Eve, which means \"All-Saints-Day\" or \"All Hallows Eve.\" The festival is celebrated on the eve of the feast of All Saints',NULL,NULL),(67939,79,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Breezy Breakfast Radio - October 30, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 10:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-09 04:38:32',NULL,'Fazzari ran down Morris Street and died on the front porch in Morris Street. He moved back to the city after being detained for a while. He ran away with a woman who was running a boarding house. She was named Bessie. She had two children who were assumed to be middle-class Jewish girls. She left them with her husband and her two children. She ran away to Hamilton with Perry. He became one of the most successful legger in the city. Bessie\'s story surprised Perry because he was a very different person from Verroni. He carried all the family grudges against Verroni in Italy. He didn\'t lay aside that Perry was more a business man. He looked it. He worked with blacks, he worked with northern Italians, even worked with Americans. He knew that he had to put it aside. Verroni was indiscriminate in killing people. He had his own group of people who would go missing. Perry continued to rise. Bessie told her grandfather that she worked for him and she went looking for him. She told him that they needed to make money and besides Perry was a nice guy. They went inside Perry\'s home and then Bessie told him what was going on. They didn\'',NULL,'Bessie\'s story surprised Perry because she was a very different person from Verroni (13 minute read)'),(67940,79,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Breezy Breakfast Radio - October 30, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-09 04:22:41',NULL,'This week\' s episode of the Breezy breakfast takes place in Guelph and features three guests: Susan Radcliffe, who will be on-air, Jay Walking, who has included a spooky dress code around the city, and Bonnie Derthnall. Phil Ault welcomes everyone to the show and begins by acknowledging the city\'s rich Indigenous history. The city has served as a refuge for many generations of people, but more specifically for the Anorwandrung and Haudenosaune. This land is part of the treaty lands of the Mississaugas. The guests are invited to hear stories of the past from three great guests, but the guests are free to express their own opinions. Phil notes that the show is a special one because it is a holiday, and he feels that this is his favorite of the year',NULL,'The Breezy Breakfast: Guelph, Canada (Sponsor)'),(67950,1438,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Worst Responders - October 30, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 09:57:37',NULL,'In this episode, Carissa and Renee discuss their show, \"Worst Responders.\" The show is a satirical comedy about horror movies and their problems.\n\nIt is a comedy that is in good fun, but it does not represent the opinions of the College. It also does not support \"murder, ghouls, or goblins,\" or any other visitors who \"maim or otherwise injure human mortals.\" Carissa says she never really thought about Halloween and that she is excited to discuss the \"maiming\" of humans. She has dressed up as a \"Cthulhuth,\" a \"weird\" creature, and she says that she would pass for a normal human being if she were dressed in a costume that didn\'t look like a haggard old man.\n\nShe also says that her favorite thing about Halloween was when she was with a friend and they would have kids come to their house to get candy. She says that was the \"first time\" she got the \"joy\" of Halloween. She loves children who don\'t have a clue what is going on and who just stare at her dead-eyed because they haven\'t yet figured out what\'s going on.',NULL,NULL),(67951,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Democracy Now - October 30, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 09:47:24',NULL,'Israel has killed more than 8,000 Palestinians, including 3,500 children, in its latest attack on the Gaza Strip. The United Nations says the siege of the coastal territory has reached its breaking point. Families of Israeli prisoners held by Hamas call on the government to exchange their loved ones for the prisoners. Meanwhile, Prime Minister BenjaminNetanyahu has apologized on social media after he published a statement blaming the attack on civilians. The Palestinian death toll has reached 111, and seven settlers have been killed, including Bila Saleh. On October 30, Israeli bulldozers demolished a memorial for a slain journalist in the West Bank.',NULL,NULL),(67961,206,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/dgvbjv/October_28th_2023_The_Minx_Sessionsa9qp7.mp3','2023-10-30 19:19:51',287962512,'2023-11-17 09:37:54',NULL,'The host of the underground music station, CIUT 8, introduces himself to his listeners and tells them that he\'s just getting started. He wants to thank them for listening to his show, which is packed with independent artists and music from all over the world.\n\nHe\'s going to kick things off tonight with a \"little boogie\" and a \"really awesome drummer bass piece\" by an artist named \"Mikel Sessions.\" The show is going to continue on Fridays from midnight until 2am. The host also tells us that he has added all of the links to all the music that he plays on his show. He also says that he wants to play Tom Hates\'s music now.',NULL,NULL),(67962,247,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ihtvqc/October_28th_2023_Calling_All_Blues6qtfp.mp3','2023-10-30 19:24:32',143961989,'2023-11-15 01:05:42',NULL,'The next segment of the program is called \"Calling All Blues.\" It\'s all about the music and the people that are playing it. It starts off with a conversation about a singer named Shakur Saeedas second track, and then it turns to a conversation between Bill Withers and Susie Vinnick, who are both playing some blues. The conversation then turns to an old friend named Eugene Smith, who used to play the tenor guitar with his brothers. Now that he\'s dead, he\'ll be playing the kalimba again.',NULL,NULL),(67963,37839,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Feeding Tummies and Souls - October 30, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-15 00:56:19',NULL,'After a few years of living with his stepdad and stepmom, David decides to return to Canada. He loves coming home for Canada Day. The fireworks are his favorite. When he turns 16, his step dad and mom separate. David moves back to Canada with his dad, step mom, three younger siblings and his two teenage brothers. He begins counseling with a woman at Kids\'Ability, who is wheelchair-bound. The woman makes an impact on David\'s life.\n\nWhen David graduates from high school, he receives the Optimist Award for overcoming adversity. He is given a pass to attend his graduation ceremony, but returns to Polarwood for the night because of his second bout of depression. He enrolls in an early childhood program at Conestog College. He finds a mentor at Action Program Read who encourages him to follow his dreams. He volunteers at daycare and in elementary schools when he turns 18. He graduates from the program when he is 18.',NULL,NULL),(67964,37839,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Feeding Tummies and Souls - October 30, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-15 00:42:26',NULL,'The program opens with a description of the event, which was originally presented as a benefit for the Harvest Market. The program is a mix of poetry, spoken word, and storytelling. It is also a celebration of National Indigenous History month. The stories will be told from the point of view of five young people who were forced to live in a residential school.\n\nThe audience will be able to donate to the Harvest market directly. The performers will also have a chance to chat with the audience during the performances. The live performers will be turning off the live chat during their performances. As a thank you for listening, the program ends with a brief interview with Jenny Mitchell, the volunteer and mobile studio coordinator at CFRU. Jenny is on parental leave and has just returned to her job.',NULL,NULL),(67974,196,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/rcyuq3/October_29_2023_Across_the_Universeakhzr.mp3','2023-10-30 20:09:29',431961989,'2023-11-15 00:31:09',NULL,'This is a special edition of the Sunday morning program on the free-form, open-air, FM radio station, CIUT 89.5. The program is all about the fall campaign, \"The Sound of your City,\" which will take place beginning on November 13th and concluding on November 19th.\n\nThe station will need your financial support to continue to serve the community and to provide listeners with the best of the best. If you\'re a regular listener of the station, then you already know all about it. But there are some people who are new to the station and they\'re only listening for a short period of time. So they need to make a donation. To do this, you can go to the website and sign up for the program. This is the first program of the day and it\'s all about raising money for the station. It\'s a celebration of his mother\'s life.',NULL,'The Toronto Tabla\'s narrator tells listeners about their new album and their live show'),(67975,81,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/The Sentinel’s Marvellous Kaleidoscope - October 30, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-15 00:21:31',NULL,'This is a little bit of a mouthful, but it\'s what we\'ve got to hear here: the first track on the new album is a remix of a piece from Solace Shard by Output 111.\n\nAfter that, we have a bunch of other stuff: the Victoria BC avant-garde experimental sound composer Marlen Arroma, the purveyors of free Will, the original track from their new Rolling Pathetique album, the track Man from the new Gold album, and the song from Kim Petras\'s new album, In the next life. The second track is a shortcut from Jenny is a witch, followed by another shortcut from The Riveen, and then the fifth track is from Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder, a new EP from Gold.',NULL,NULL),(67976,1591,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/New or Never - October 30, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-15 00:09:55',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(67986,83,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/to know the land - October 30, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-15 00:01:14',NULL,'In this chapter, the UM talks about his love for stories. He loves the fact that the stories can be repeated endlessly. But sometimes, stories are lost, and the themes that are there are lost. For example, he has been looking for stories about tracking signs of animals.\n\nHe knows stories like the Volscian Saga or the Beowulf. There are elements of this, but it\'s hard to find them. One of the themes he\'s looking for lately is stories about mushrooms. He\'s read a lot of books about the cultural value of mushrooms, but there aren\'t any stories about them in the stories. There\'s one of his favorite stories, which is about a young woman picking mushrooms. The young woman learns about the plants from the snakes that she encounters in the forest.',NULL,NULL),(67987,82,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Big Sis Radio - October 30, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 17:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-14 23:46:52',NULL,'On this week\'s edition of Big Sis Jobs Radio, the narrator is psyched to get dressed up for Halloween. He\'s dressed as Steve Jobs, an iPod guy, and he\'s got a new trick up his sleeve: a black shirt and running shoes.\n\nThe narrator also has some scary songs to play, including a song about a haunted house and a song called \"I Don\'t like my mind\" by Mitzki. The song is about how our minds are full of all kinds of scary things, and that\'s scary. The next song is \"Haunted House on Zillow\" by The Garden and it\'s about how scary it is everywhere. This is a reminder that the world is scary, but it shouldn\'t scare you.',NULL,NULL),(67997,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Blues Around the Block - October 30, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 23:35:09',NULL,'Mac Dee is a new host of Blues Around The Block. He\'s got a new name, but he\'s also got a bunch of old favorites. He starts off with Hamilton City\'s Smoke Wagon Blues Band, which is a band from the old days. Then, Tinsley Ellis, Just Like Rain, and Tommy Castro finish off the show.\n\nMac Dee wants to go home, so he starts with Kenny Neal\'s \"It Don\'t cost anything it don\'t-cost anything and spread a little love / Then Selwyn / Burchwood from June 2023 release of alligator records / Call me what you want / And Susan Tedesschi from September 2023 release/ On fantasy records/ Can\'t you leave you alone\" . This is all from CFRU\'s 93.3 FM. MacDee also starts with Kristin Ingram, aka Kingfish, from his September 23rd release on alligator-records live in London.',NULL,NULL),(67998,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Blues Around the Block - October 30, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 19:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-14 23:26:24',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68008,85,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Ripcord Radio - October 30, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 23:17:13',NULL,'In this episode, the gang continues its program with a look at some of the latest metal acts. We start off with Denmark, who have a song called \"Trick or Treat\" from their latest album.\n\nThey also hear a song from Motorhead called \"I\'m your witch doctor\" and a song by the late great Eddie Clark called \"Motorhead with i\'m / Your witch doctor\". They hear a cover of John Mayall\'s \"Blues\" from the band Beer Drinkers And Hell Raisers. And finally they hear \"GBH with lycanthropy\" from Birmingham England. The band originally came together in 1980 under the name Fast Boys. They were not able to celebrate their 40th anniversary due to travel restrictions imposed by the CoVID-19 pandemic, but they have been busy touring ever since. They put on a great show here in Guelph in October as part of their tour celebrating the anniversary of their 33rd album City Babies Revenge. The next song is from the Los Angeles band Nice Blitz. The song comes from an EP called Not Lockdown. The first song we hear is from an album called All Serious Seriousness Aside. The second song is about a fictional murderer. The third song is a',NULL,NULL),(68009,86,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/The Deep House Project - October 30, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 22:00:00',86638720,'2023-10-31 04:56:55',NULL,'The show kicks off with a music selection from the 90s. It\'s called Future Shock and it\'s a horror movie set in a virtual reality world. It also has a book and a short movie about how people get stressed and paralyzed by too much change. The music is all about going back and forth in time. Way back, way back. Way way back, Way back! Way back... Way back. The group then goes back in time to listen to a song called Spooky Cowboy, which sounds very much like a mass-produced costume. The song basically says, \"I\'m not a cowboy, I\'ve got a plan. I\'ll never be wrong.\"',NULL,'Future Shock is a horror movie set in a virtual reality world. Way back, way back'),(68019,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/CFRU Playlist - October 31, 2023 at 06:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 06:00:00',86638720,'2023-10-31 14:06:18',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(68020,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - October 31, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 23:56:30',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68021,87,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Back in the USSR - October 30, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 22:49:56',NULL,'In this Dispatches, the human rights journalist and author of the book, The Return of the Detainee, discusses Israel\'s recent war in the Gaza Strip with journalist and documentary maker, Abi Martin. She also discusses her latest work, which is called \"Gaza Frights For Freedom,\" which was released four years ago and continues to be an important part of the discourse on the situation in the Middle East.',NULL,NULL),(68023,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Rainbow Country - October 31, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 22:39:52',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68024,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Rainbow Country - October 31, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 00:00:00',86507648,