,'',NULL,NULL),(68131,38669,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/NOSFERATU! - November 1, 2023 at 02:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 02:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 08:28:52',NULL,'As the war continues in the Gaza Strip, the United Nations Childrens Agency warns that Israel is committing \"rampant grave violations\" of children\'s rights. An Israeli warplane has attacked the Turkish- Palestinian Friendship Hospital, which serves as the sole hospital in the besieged territory for cancer treatment. The hospital has also been destroyed by the attack. The Israeli Prime Minister, Benjamin Netanyahu, has rejected a ceasefire call, saying that Israel will not surrender to Hamas or to terrorism. In response, Hamas has released a prisoner-confession video in which three Israeli women are held captive. The release of the women comes as the Israeli army threatens the family of the Gaza correspondent of El Jazeera, Yumna El Sayed.',NULL,NULL),(68132,38669,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/NOSFERATU! - November 1, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 01:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-14 08:16:00',NULL,'This program is a continuation of the program that was originally aired on CFRU 91.3. The show opens with a message from a man named Bahamudah, who is a deaf man. His name is Pops, and he is the host of the Morning Soul-Shake-Up. He asks his son how he is feeling, and Pops answers that he is fine.\n\nBefore he can continue, however, he is interrupted by an urgent message from Canada. The message is from Mad Canada, and it is from the Ad Council and the Pivotal Ventures, who are supporting Sounded Out, a national campaign to raise awareness of the dangers of impaired boating. The program ends with a reminder that the Alzheimer\'s society of Waterloo Wellington has a music project to help people with dementia. They need volunteers to help set up an iPod, play music, and create playlists. The project is free of charge and provides a personalized playlist for people living with the disease. The organization is also looking for people who want to donate money, iPods, or gift cards.',NULL,NULL),(68159,180,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/5pa2jd/HOWL_-_OCTOBER_31_2023a7xg1.mp3','2023-11-01 12:22:59',56689813,'2023-11-14 08:06:35',NULL,'This is the first episode of the new music show on Hal 895. It is called \"The Halloween Open Mic\" and it is hosted by the man who hosts the show, a musician named \"Valentino Assenza.\" He is a musician who lives on Turtle Island, an island off the coast of Nova Scotia in Canada. He is known for playing music that is both \"adult\" and \"sexy.\" He plays music that has a \"Tokata Fugue\" or \"Gothic\" vibe, which means \"Gothic.\" He also plays music with a Latin vibe, such as the \"Toka Fugue.\n\n\" He explains that he is a fan of horror movies, and this is a good time of year to re-watch them. He also says that the open mics that he hosts are not as popular as they once were. He received seven submissions for the open mic, and only seven people responded to his open mic. He wants to make sure that the next open mic is a success, so he\'s going to put on another open mic in November. He\'ll be holding it from 10pm to 11pm on November 28, 2023. There will be 17 minutes of submissions for that open mic and he wants',NULL,NULL),(68162,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/CFRU Playlist - November 1, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-01 14:06:12',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(68163,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - November 1, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 08:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-14 07:51:58',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68165,159,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/mzw2at/CAREER_-_CareerBuzzCIUTfinalnovember120236hvpn.mp3','2023-11-01 15:30:00',85474859,'2023-11-14 07:42:15',NULL,'On today\'s program, Hoda introduces her guests, Joe Iuiby and Dave Crumby. In the first half of the program, Joe shares valuable information about the 360-degree, and in the second half, Dave shares valuable insights on the reasons employers are using it.\n\nJoe is Chief Executive Officer and Co-Founder of Track Surveys. He works with clients to create a culture of feedback in the workplace. He has worked as a Learning and Development Director at Ernst & Young, as well as as as a Director at Fujitsu and a Learning Director at Saudi Telecom. He is also the author of a guide to success with 360 degree feedback. Joe divides his time between London, Dublin and working with clients in the Middle East, London and Woodhouse College. Joe shares his definition of a career term, and he and Hoda discuss the importance of having good work conversations.',NULL,NULL),(68166,174,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/mpv72s/November_1_2023_Global_Rhythms6aube.mp3','2023-11-01 14:05:01',431961989,'2023-11-17 09:28:25',NULL,'Ken Stauer welcomes listeners to his program on CIUT 89.5. The program opens with Stolen Moments, a song from Anushka Shankar\'s new release Chapter One Forever For Now. It is followed by The Gentle Good from Kamini Netarjan, the compositionji, and the song The Darkening. The songs follow from Wales,The Gentle Good,The Darkening, and The Long Long Rather For Light. Outta Sync is the track followed from the new release by Holly Cook.',NULL,NULL),(68175,280,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/drs9gq/Ep86_India_and_Myanmar8mjte.mp3','2023-11-01 15:12:30',84333979,'2023-11-14 07:28:16',NULL,'This is the second part of a two-part interview with Seth Martosh, a student at the University of Toronto who studies physics. The first part of the interview is with Truxell, the host of the university\'s popular radio show, Tracks From Abroad.\n\nThe second part is with Seth, who explains that the show is a way for students to travel and learn about different countries around the world. He tells us that today\'s show will be a packed show. He introduces us to Harman, an Indian student who has moved to Canada to study at the university. The show also introduces Brian Dickey, a photographer who went to Myanmar to document the revolution in the country. Then the show shifts to the topic of Seth\'s thesis, which is studying the relationship between physics and chemistry.\n\nHe explains that he studied physics in high school and he had a good teacher who motivated him to study. He says that he hated chemistry because he had bad teachers. He\'s now working on the connection between the two sciences. He wants to use electrons as a way to study proteins, and he\'s working on a new class of bacteria that\'s called mass stars.',NULL,NULL),(68176,99,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/The Stillness & The Dancing - November 1, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-07 14:34:11',NULL,'The Stillness And The Dancing is an hour long program, and it starts off with John Swank, who is a music journalist, talking about some of his favorite albums. He starts with Soundings and Fathoms, which is a collection of tracks from various artists, including Bodov Songs , Attic Reverb , and Stench Of Exist . The next release is Arrow Wounds\'s \"The Slow-Boiling-Amphibian-Dream-State,\" which is the first part of a four part album series. The second release is Hiss Tracks , whose album is called Shortwave Nights , which captures all of Godspeed\'s noisy side. The third release is Stad , an EP by a flank named Deruntin , followed by Jackson Payne\'s Leisure Time Explosion , a track from the game Mist . And the fourth release is a release by Towers , called Towers 3 .',NULL,'The Stillness And The Dancing (Sponsor), Episode 3 (Twitter Thread)'),(68177,99,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/The Stillness & The Dancing - November 1, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-07 14:24:50',NULL,'The Stillness and The Dancing opens with a spooky mix of music. It\'s a Halloween edition, which means that the show is going to be a little more sinister. The show\'s narrator explains that he\'s been living in the city during the week and is undergoing treatment for his brain tumor. He\'s grateful that he has some fresh music to share with the listeners. The first track is a new release from the band Grotto Veritano, called \"Endless Vacation.\" The second track is \"If only you knew what you claimed to.\" The third track is from Richard Skelton, \"The Inward Circle.\" The fourth track is called \"The Stillness in dancing here on CFR 93.3 . . and the localFM die all over th world through the streaming services.\" The last track is new music from Inward Circles. The narrator says that this track captures \"something kind of haunting, melodic for me.\"',NULL,'The Stillness and The Dancing (Sponsor), a Halloween spooky mix of new music '),(68187,100,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/We Know Some Stuff + CFRU playlist - November 1, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 07:15:53',NULL,'The first guest on the show is a guy named Serge, who is a student at Laurentian College. He\'s a master\'s student in electrochemistry at the university. Serge started his studies in science because he wanted to study water and how it\'s used. He wanted to work on wastewater treatment.\n\nAs he was making his way through his program, he decided to focus on microplastics. He decided to go back to school to do his masters. He went to the university to study hydroponics. Here\'s what he\'s doing: he\'ll use electrochemistry to treat hydroponics, which is basically a water-growing system. He uses electrodes to do things like chlorination, which kills microorganisms, and hydroxyl radicals, which are short-lived chemicals that kill off certain kinds of microorganisms. He also uses fluoroalkyl substances, which aren\'t as good for killing off microorganisms as fluoroquinolones, to protect hydroponics from certain types of pathogens.',NULL,NULL),(68188,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/Democracy Now - November 1, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 07:00:57',NULL,'On this edition of Democracy Now!, Amy Goodman takes us to the Besiege Territory, where we\'ll hear from a former resident of the city of Jabalia, a humanitarian advocate, and a long-time human rights attorney. Amy also talks with Craig McIvers, a former United Nations official who\'s now an attorney in New York. This is part one of a two-part program on the war and peace in the Middle East. The first part of the program is about the humanitarian situation in the besieged city of Gaza.\n\nIn the last segment, we heard about the latest developments in the war in the Gaza. Israel has struck the densely packed Jabalia Refugee Camp again, killing 50 people and injuring 150. The doctor who treated the victims of the attack at an Indonesian hospital tells us that hundreds of people have been injured, including hundreds of martyrs and children. The doctors say there\'s no way to treat them all. The only thing they can do is try to help them. The World Heath Organization warns of a public health crisis in Gaza. An engineer with Al-Jazeera\'s Gaza Bureau has lost 19 family members in the attack. Meanwhile, a deal has been reached between Qatar and Egypt to',NULL,NULL),(68191,155,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/nz33ki/DrMouth_CIUTshow_oct31_2023_fullshow.mp3','2023-11-01 19:47:30',431485568,'2023-11-14 00:57:13',NULL,'The gang gets down to business. They\'re talking about the various songs they\'re going to hear on the three-hour Halloween extravaganza. They start off by talking about how scary it is to be a rock \'n\' roll fan. They get down to the songs by the Ramones, the Ramones cover of Pet Cemetery, the Green Goblin in the animated version of Spider-Man, and Dr. Curse. Then they go on to talk about Dr. Frankenstein\'s monster, which they think will be a good idea. The gang also talks about the upcoming shows by the guys from the band called Dark Clouds. The guys will be playing three shows in Hamilton, Waterloo, and on the fourth, they\'ll be playing at a dive bar in Waterloo',NULL,NULL),(68200,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/Volunteer Playlist - November 1, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 00:41:59',NULL,'I can make... I can do it... I\'ll do it. And I can tell you that you\'re going to find your way, too. \"I can make it,\" says Dr. Rivers. \"It\'s just a matter of finding your way.\"',NULL,NULL),(68210,102,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/End Credits - November 1, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 15:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-02 02:17:32',NULL,'The credits of this program are a local movie talk show hosted by Adam Donaldson and Peter Westie. The show starts off with a discussion about the recent spate of deaths in the entertainment industry. The first show topic is \"feel-good\" movies, which are comedies that make you feel better. The second show topic deals with \"the axe gang\" a term used for a martial arts group that originated in Hong Kong in the early 20th century. The third show topic relates to a recent Martin Scorsese movie, \"Hugo,\" a story about an orphan boy named Hugo. It is set in the Paris train station in 1922 and tells the story of the invention of the cinema.',NULL,'The \'feel-good\' movie talk show begins with a discussion about the recent spate of deaths in the entertainment industry'),(68211,1464,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/Gryphon And Special Olympics Sports Show - November 1, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-02 02:07:19',NULL,'In this program, Taylor introduces his guests and then introduces himself as the host of the Griffin Sports Show. He introduces Dizeng as a star point guard on the University of Guelph\'s men\'s and women\'s basketball, and as a member of the University\'s National Art Basketball Rookie team. He also talks about his hometown, Hamilton, and his experience playing against Team Canada star Shay Goodes Alexander at the last summer\'s London Games. He discusses his expectations for the upcoming season and his hopes of making the Canadian Basketball League team.',NULL,'Taylor is the host of the Griffin Sports Show. He’s a point guard at the University of Guelph'),(68212,13298,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/CFRU Selector - November 1, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 17:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-02 01:57:28',NULL,'We start this program with an interview with Doug Blackwith, host of the old time music program \"Sounds Like Old Times\" on CFRU 92.3. He tells us that he\'s been entertaining listeners with old songs and stories since the early 1900s. He\'s hosting a show on the 4th of November at the Al Green Theatre, a venue accessible to people with physical limitations. The show will be a benefit for the War Amputees, who need artificial limbs and equipment to live with amputation. If you\'re a war amputee and you want to help, visit waramps.ca. The song opens with a poem called \"The Story is Ours.\" It\'s about a man named \"Patient\" who is a patient in a war hospital. \"Patient,\" the song says, \"do you touch the sun. Do you realize sun. show my light. make the world my sun. Still light as soonas we agree Patient.\" The song ends with a quote from the poem \"The sun is near you. It\'ll not always be there on the opposite side.\"',NULL,'\'Sounds Like Old Times\': \'Do you touch the sun. Do you realize sun\''),(68222,105,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/B Siide Radio - November 1, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-02 03:27:42',NULL,'Stash Ram is back in the States. He\'s back to robbing. He has a new plan: he\'s going to start a new gang of robbers. This time, he\'ll be back to \"live like an orphan\" . He doesn\'t want to live like a homeless man. He is going to hit the road with a shotgun, and he can\'t even run with it. So, he needs to figure out a way to keep people on their toes. Stash Ram points out that the \"cats that be hating\" still love the dogs, even though they know that they\'re doomed to die by the law. He tells them that he got them all on the same team: \"you got money keep yours\" , and since Stash Ram took the governor\'s job, \"even the cats that are hating\" are still loving the dogs. He explains that he likes to use a watch as a weapon and a gun as a way of killing people. He compares his methods to the \"riots\" in a jailhouse. He buys an extra 20 bucks with the money, which he then uses to buy some drugs. He says that he can kill anyone he wants, even cats',NULL,'Stash Ram is back in the States and is going to start a new gang of robbers'),(68223,106,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/Trail Mix - November 1, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-02 03:16:24',NULL,'The Underground Man returns with a new song from a band called Thresh. The song is called \"Closing on a minor client\" and it opens with the words, \"True love is easy. It\'s easy to know it\'s true in the end. True love is the only thing that matters in the world. It is easy in the classic. I\'m just an alien horse power like an Mongolian trying to find soul. I can\'t complain though, as I am only an alien power trying to search soul again. The Underground Men also play a new track from Micaiah Mc-Raven\'s new album \"In These Times\" and a song from Panisaurus\'s \"Market Street Junkie\" from his new album.',NULL,'The Underground Man returns with a new song from a band called Thresh'),(68224,1321,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/Hong Kong Student Radio Association - November 1, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 11:23:50',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Hong Kong Student Association Various From the Roots Up CIUT 89.4 CFRU archives'),(68234,107,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/Tone Zone - November 1, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-02 04:38:49',NULL,'The show starts off with a rendition of one of Nirvana\'s most famous songs, \"In utero Scentless Apprentice,\" which was released in September of 1994 and is a live version. The show also includes a number of other songs from the band\'s career, including \"Pink Flag,\" \"Wire and mannequin,\" and \"The go-between\'s\" and \"Bachelor kisses.\" The show closes with a song from a band called \"Ducks limited,\" which is a new single from Matt Webb and Bry Webb, the twin brothers who have sold millions of records for their roles in the music industry.',NULL,'Nirvana\'s \"In utero Scentless Apprentice\" is a live version of the band'),(68244,97,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/Wild Combination - November 2, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 04:17:28',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68254,97,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/Wild Combination - November 2, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 04:17:07',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68274,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - November 2, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 00:06:38',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68275,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/Here Today - November 2, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-07 05:00:20',NULL,'Aaron Badgley is back on the show to introduce us to some of the new artists on the air. He starts off with a few covers, including Martha Johnson and the Muffins from Buffalo Springfield and Martha Johnson, Mark Gain, John Orpheus and Sam and Casey Exists from Cover Rama, a compilation of artists who cover songs they really like. Aaron also introduces us to Paul Manchin, who is releasing his new album soon and has a new song called First on it. Finally, Aaron introduces you to Church of Trees, who have a new single out called Pet Cemetery. Aaron and his friend Jenna also introduce you to a new EP from RewindStar called Forward.',NULL,'Aaron Badgley on the Weeknight Show (Sponsor)'),(68279,173,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/brrwxz/Club_Ned_Nov_5_2023_podcastbobye.mp3','2023-11-02 14:11:35',463090415,'2023-11-13 23:58:06',NULL,'The next morning, the community radio show starts up with a bang. It\'s a big fundraiser for the station. It starts off with a bunch of local acts, and then it goes to some random acts from all over the city. They start off with IBO, who\'s called Asterekeow. Then we hear from DeVito, who did For The Road, from Wale, Wale who did The Road and from Prudence who did \"Nana 2-4\" . And then it\'s all about the Greenbelt Land, which is a big deal. It turns out that Ford had meetings with some of the people who were going to be paid off by the land deal, and he\'d have to pay off all of them in cash.',NULL,NULL),(68286,219,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/w5nzsq/ES231101.mp3','2023-11-02 14:38:25',139549345,'2023-11-13 23:42:54',NULL,'The program opens with a description of the music that will be on the show. The first track is called \"Light Machine\" and the second track is \"Infinity Plus One\" by Jennifer Wilson. The third track is from a group called Sick Boss, which includes Peggy Lee and Josh Zubat, and is described as an \"ornithopter\" .',NULL,NULL),(68287,111,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/Tales from the Bridge - November 2, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 09:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-13 23:29:52',NULL,'In this episode, Sam and Tristan discuss what they read this summer. They also discuss the science fiction they\'ve been reading, including a book by Stanislau Lem, Solaris. Sam also reads some of the books in the Expansive series.',NULL,NULL),(68288,112,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/FoodFarm Talk - November 2, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 23:18:34',NULL,'In this episode of the Canadian Food Focus podcast, host Clinton Machuck talks with nutritionist, Erin McGregor, about how to recognize food misinformation. In particular, he discusses how to spot false and misleading information on food labels, social media, and other sources of information. She explains that she has worked as a dietician for over 15 years and has done many other interesting things as well. She previously worked in a nutrition communications company where she wrote a cookbook for Canadians. Her goal was to encourage people to cook and prepare their own food and to make informed decisions about food, rather than fear it. She also works to help people recognize what is true, what is not, and what is an exaggeration about food.',NULL,NULL),(68298,195,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/kvdkdi/Dementia13RadioShow_23_10_31.mp3','2023-11-02 17:58:12',287962512,'2023-11-13 23:04:23',NULL,'This is the first of a series of short stories that will appear in the next two volumes of the novel. The first part of the story is set in the early 20th century, and it tells the story of a young man who falls in love with a woman who is the mother of his cousin. The young woman, Mary Day, is the wife of the man who is his lover, and the young man is the father of his child. The narrator explains that Mary Day is a witch, and that she is the only woman who has ever loved a man as her lover.',NULL,NULL),(68299,296,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/aztb3w/3rd_Face_21_oct_2023ae8yt.mp3','2023-11-02 17:47:47',143961989,'2023-11-13 22:49:55',NULL,'The third face on the show is screaming out to everyone on the ship. He\'s sure it\'s from Shakespeare, but he\'s also sure that there\'s a witch who has to make a soup for a maiden like he always does. The narrator is a bit worried about the fact that everyone says he\'ll always be another number. The tide\'s on unsteady legs, and the boy invited to a christening is a little wet with mercury. The Mad Hatter is a bed wetter. The fingerless wonder is a name and a reason to call home. The next song is about an ear strike. He can visualize the cold. He imagines that it\'ll come out at night, and he sees flashes of light. He gets the atlas tattooed on his back. He wishes he knew it like he knew his face. The sailors have been napping and everyone is heading down to the ship, and they\'ve got a name for it.',NULL,NULL),(68300,90,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/Bridging The Social Distance - November 2, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 22:37:08',NULL,'The interview is with Jenny Mitchell, a volunteer and studio coordinator at CFRU, who is a part of the Guelph Neighborhoods Support Coalition, which runs a weekly market in the North End of town called the NorthEnd Harvest Market. It offers free fresh produce to those in need. It also has a resource fair every year where other organizations can come and set up a booth. Jenny encourages listeners to visit the GuelphNeighborhoodsSupportCoalition.org to learn more about the market and to get more information. The interview ends with Chelsea, a community engagement coordinator with the Guelph Wellington Poverty Elimination Task Force. She is a member of the task force and works in the City of Guelph and the Counties of Wellington and Guelph. The task force works to eliminate poverty in Wellington County by advocating for resources and solutions at a systemic level. In other words, they advocate for a system-based approach to poverty elimination.',NULL,NULL),(68301,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/Democracy Now - November 2, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 22:26:05',NULL,'On this week\'s program, we hear more about the humanitarian crisis in the war-ravaged Gaza Strip. In the last few days, Israel has killed 195 Palestinians, including a hundred and twenty-two who are feared dead. A school run by the United Nations Relief and Works Agency for Palestine Refugees in the Near East has also been hit. The only hospital in the besieged territory has closed, and the only fuel it has is running on is running out. Meanwhile, Israel\'s troops and tanks have been advancing deeper into the territory. Vice President Joe Biden has spoken out for a humanitarian pause in the fighting. In Minneapolis, a Jewish rabbi interrupts a speech by a local council on American Islamic Relations leader and calls for a ceasefire. When she asks for a pause, the vice president says he supports a pause. In Minnesota, a chapter of the Council of American-Islamic relations holds protests demanding a ceasefire, while in Rhode Island peace activists hold a rally outside the office of Senator Jack Reed urging him not to send more money to Israel.',NULL,NULL),(68304,169,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/awk76d/IW_30th_Oct67yaf.mp3','2023-11-02 19:19:12',143961989,'2023-11-13 22:15:29',NULL,'This is the first time we\'ve heard the name \"Indigenous Waves\" on the show, and it\'s because we\'re talking about one territory. Yup, the Yup\'it territory of Canada. We\'ll get to that in a second. This time, we\'ll talk about the different aspects of the show: the show is called \"Indigenous Indigenous Waves\" and it airs on CIUT. It\'s a student-run station, so all of the students are listening to the show. The show is hosted by Jenny Blackbird, who\'s not really a student. She\'s just a friend of the station. She says she likes the show because it doesn\'t require her to be a student to listen to the program. We get to talk about some of the other things that are going on at the school: the U of T\'s annual Indigenous Fashion Week, which is being held this week, and a workshop with an Inuk beauty named Amanda. She was the one who created all the makeup for the pandemic, and she did a lot of the Inuk\'s tick box. The students watched some creepy videos about the Inuit fear of getting eaten or tickled, and then listened to her',NULL,NULL),(68305,171,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/untikw/podbean_version8207k.mp3','2023-11-02 18:17:03',186748977,'2023-11-13 21:58:27',NULL,'The narrator describes a family tradition. His name is Brad, and he and the overseer are sitting in the chair of the overseer at five oclock listening to an alternative radio. The narrator says that it is nearing the time of winter, and that the animals are gathering for the winter season. He says that a song is playing in the background, and then he is gone. The moon is gone, and the dust is brittle. It turns to ash and brittlestaccato dust',NULL,NULL),(68306,158,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/6bhsnh/The_Radical_Rev_31_octazttt.mp3','2023-11-02 19:14:16',143961989,'2023-11-13 21:48:02',NULL,'The Radical Reverends show welcomes a second guest, Reverend Christine Smallwood. She is a minister who has been doing funerals for many years. She tells a story about a funeral she had to attend where the casket fit on her lap. She also tells about her favorite funeral, which was the one of Johnny Cash. She explains that funerals are one of the most meaningful ministry in a minister\'s life because they allow people to be vulnerable and share their deepest thoughts. She says she has refused to play a particular song during a funeral when someone requested \"Highway to Hell\" because she has never considered it a sentiment, but she says she could not condone such a sentiment. The show ends with a discussion of the idea that people condemn one another to hell.',NULL,NULL),(68314,189,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/92umzu/VFTC_Nov19k1ru.mp3','2023-11-02 18:37:47',281111040,'2023-11-13 21:36:36',NULL,'The host of the underground show Vinyl from the strontium welcomes his listeners to a new live show. He thanks Peter and Andrew for coming to his show last week and thanks Philip for another episode of his show. The host also thanks his listeners for their continued support of the station. He says that he now comes up with a new theme for the live show, but he doesn\'t yet know what it is. He\'s going to let the listeners hang around and figure it out. There are three great progressive bands starting tonight. The first band is Blue Oyster Cult, the second is Metallica, and the third is Yes. The show starts with a veteran of psychic warfare on CIUT 99.5 FM. The veteran is Kirk Hammett. The band\'s latest album is called Too Far Gone. The song is called Lucky Man. The lead singer of Lucky Man was Greg Lake. The ELP song was called Lucky Woman. The drummer of Lucky Woman was Karl Palmer.',NULL,NULL),(68315,209,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/83wyjq/TO_Nov_1st7sppy.mp3','2023-11-02 19:17:45',143961989,'2023-11-13 21:20:23',NULL,'Enneke Hamilton, host of Turn Out Radio, welcomes guests to the program, including award-winning choreographer, dancer, and teacher Terrile McGuire, and Carol, a music and dance teacher. Terrile discusses her health and her concern for the world\'s climate. She says she is grateful to be safe, not suffering from any of the disasters that are occurring around the world.',NULL,NULL),(68316,205,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/sfyqm5/November_2nd_2023_Music_at_High_Noon9wr3o.mp3','2023-11-02 18:17:16',227371264,'2023-11-13 21:07:16',NULL,'This week\'s program starts off with Pigeons Playing Ping Pong and ends with King Buffalo\'s song Regenerator. This is the second week in a row that Mike has selected music for the program. This time, the music starts with Pigeon Playing Ping-Pong and ends up with King-Buffin\'s \"Regenerator\" . If you\'re looking for more music this week, check out this playlist. It goes like this: Pigeon Playing Pong Elephante Friendship Club Flat Five Dumpstefunk Pure Beauty Ski School Bend Sinister What It Takes Leila Zoe & Henrik Freislauter Dark Heart Milspec Too Long at The Fair Hashderoid Freak Power Howling Giant Glass Future',NULL,NULL),(68317,218,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/wdv2z7/The_Taylor_Report_5-6pm9612u.mp3','2023-11-02 19:21:04',143961989,'2023-11-13 20:56:32',NULL,'In this brief interview with Phil Conant