 to you.\" We also hear some familiar music from Bri Webb and his crew. The show also includes some music from Thievery Corporation, a Lebanese-Lebanese artist. The program ends with a discussion about the upcoming 12th International Film Festival. The festival will feature a number of documentaries, including one about July Talk, a satirical band that played the Stardust drive in the original Broadway production of Beauty and the Beast back in the early 2000s.',NULL,NULL),(68324,182,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/sgbyih/NBR_Nov_1_202384rgg.mp3','2023-11-02 21:26:58',144160391,'2023-11-13 18:26:21',NULL,'On this week\'s edition of No Beat Radio, host Minesh introduces the show and announces that he hopes listeners will sign up to be a member of the Canadian Institution for the Untied. He also announces that a band called Offworld will be playing a show in Toronto this week. The show will also feature a band from London called Mono Negatives. The band will also be playing at a club called Strewdattari on November 4th. The only thing left to do is to check out nobeatradio.com, the Facebook page, and the Soundcloud page.',NULL,NULL),(68330,289,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/edqh74/The_Next_Stop_1239y95k.mp3','2023-11-02 21:02:06',272565842,'2023-11-13 18:15:15',NULL,'The Next Stop On Ciut.FM The next stop on this Halloween special edition is the next station. This is where we\'re going to hear three tracks from the horror film The Thing, composer John Carpenter\'s first foray into the genre, and the haunting music of legendary composer and horror film maker N. E.O.Morricone. The third track is a song from the Carpenter film To Max Shaq, written by John Carpenter, his son Cody, and his godson Daniel. It\'s from the movie The Thing. Next up is Flatline from DJ Roswell, followed by the Witches from Bengal, Sam the Sham from the Pharaohs, the Sonics and the Witch from the Witchboard, Susie from the Banshees, Round Robin from the Wolfman, and David Bowie from Scary Monsters and the Super Creeps. And finally, Jim Blazer and John Harrison from the 1985 film Day Of The Dead. The show ends with the classic \"It\'s homage\" theme from the \"Simpsons Halloween special\" .',NULL,NULL),(68331,115,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/RadiOPIRG - November 2, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 15:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-13 18:01:03',NULL,'Oprah Guelph is now accepting applications for the Rebel Knowledge 2024 Symposium. This year\'s theme will be \"food and housing insecurity\", and the organization is looking for people to help organize the event. If you\'re looking for a position, check out the organization\'s website for details. Or, if you\'d like to help with the planning of the event, apply to be the external coordinator of the conference. The deadline for applications is November 6th, so if you know someone who\'d be interested in applying, you can let them know through either of the organizations\' mailing lists. Finally, Oprah Guelph announces that there are still spaces available for the next Rebel Knowledge Symposium, which will be held in 2024. In the meantime, there are lots of great jobs out there for people who want to help people in Guelph and beyond.',NULL,NULL),(68332,116,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/T.K.O. - November 2, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 17:51:12',NULL,'The guys discuss the past week, which has been full of activity. The guys also give a shout-out to a friend, Karen Tran, who hosted a party for the weekend. The girls talk about how they\'re going to dress up for Halloween, what they\'ll do with themselves, and whether or not they should get some candy. Karen also explains that she went to the store to pick up some candy for the kids in her neighborhood, but everything was gone, so she only had two packets of stuff. She\'s sorry she couldn\'t give more candy to the kids, but she\'ll still give out treats to her family and friends.',NULL,NULL),(68342,118,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/Open Sources Guelph - November 2, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 17:37:09',NULL,'On this week\'s Open Source, Scott Hertz, the host of the CFRU 98.3 FM show, and Adam Donaldson, host of CFRU.tv\'s Political and Current Affairs Discussion Show, discuss Mariah Carey\'s announcement that the season is here, and how she plans to break out of her \"cryogenic chamber\" and announce that the \"season has begun\" on November 1. They discuss the recent passing of a carbon tax in Guelph, and the fact that a group of citizens has released a huge document dump showing that the provincial government did not have the resources to regulate the growth of the green belt. The documents also show that the premier, Doug Ford, was talking to the people of the province about how to \"shave the greenbelt\" and \"build on it\" in order to benefit himself and his friends.',NULL,NULL),(68343,119,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/Turtle Island Underground - November 2, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 17:26:10',NULL,'This episode opens with Mac describing Turtle Island Underground as an \"indigenous alternative\" on the campus. Mac introduces Jaredfeathers as the lead singer from the new album from the Blackfoot storyteller. He also introduces the band Senua, an \"atmospheric black metal\" band. The band is led by singer Tanaia, who describes the band\'s songs as \"Post-rock and Post-metal\" in a way that sounds like a mix of the two. He tells us that the song that sticks out to him most is \"My dad Showed Me one time\" by the band.',NULL,NULL),(68345,161,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/abezaj/VientoSur-November-4th-2023.mp3','2023-11-03 00:59:34',87777764,'2023-11-13 17:12:06',NULL,'The music begins with a Boligian musician named Willie Rios who is a master of the Charango, a traditional Andean instrument. Willie is a native of Sucre in the province of Bolivia and he has composed two songs for the program. The music then moves to another musician named Boliviamanta, who played music from the different regions of Bolivia. Then they move on to the charango, another traditional instrument from the region. The first song is Nucalata and the second is Yaki. The third song is Canva Cusa, a song from the song Boligiamattana. The last song is Noches de Amor. The musicians then move to another band named Ricciari who plays music from La Paz. The songs they play are Charanguita, Chajhuanto, El Pototheto, Contregiadad, and Cyrina del Tambien. The band also has a song called Nino and Yocente. The narrator tells us that the band will be raising money to keep the program going every Saturday morning at 10 to 11 so that they can keep up with the latest developments in the music world.',NULL,NULL),(68354,120,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/The Crooked Beat - November 2, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-13 16:59:49',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68355,120,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/The Crooked Beat - November 2, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 16:53:46',NULL,'This week\'s edition of The Crooked Beat features a bunch of new releases, including tracks from Escape Roots from Scotland, the Human Rights album Reggae Strong from Freddie McGregor, and new tracks from G-Potato Ranks, Jimmy Cliff, and Bishob. The band also includes Susan Kudogan, who\'s a regular on the show. She\'s also the host of the show, and she\'s got a list of artists she\'d like to hear on the next show. The list includes: BISHOB, Meta, and The Cornerstones from Brooklyn, the KRS-Ones from New York, and a remix from Bobby Brown.',NULL,NULL),(68365,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/Forever Deaf - November 2, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 16:41:53',NULL,'The show introduces its first host, Dean, who tells the audience that he\'s got an hour plus he got midnight and he got one hour. He finishes playing some songs for the show, which includes Doria, Atria, Artach, and Dysmorphia. He also announces that a Halloween party is coming up at Red Papaya, and he\'ll be there. Then he announces a concert for November 11th. He announces that Boffold, a band from Toronto, will be playing there. He says that the band used to perform in front of the city hall, but they were banned from doing so by the city. He then plays two songs from Boffolds, Stoned and Black Sabbath. And finally, he announces that he has used a new drug, CBD oil, to treat a tumor in his neck. He gives us a little background on the tumor: it\'s called Geoblastoma, and it was discovered by Tragically Hip\'s Gord Downie. It involves a tumor that\'s on his spine.',NULL,NULL),(68366,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/Volunteer Playlist - November 2, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 18:49:33',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68376,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Forever Deaf - November 3, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 00:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-13 16:21:29',NULL,'This is the second hour of the midnight hour, and it\'s the hour when bands stop playing and start playing again. This hour is dedicated to anniversary releases. The first one is from Montrose, which is 50 years old, and the second is from Merciful Fate, which has just turned 40 years old and is also celebrating its 40th anniversary. The last release is from Anthrax and it is called Confession. It is about a female vocalist named Joy Belladonna, who is also a member of the band.',NULL,NULL),(68377,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/Forever Deaf - November 2, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 16:12:20',NULL,'The Underground Man returns to the Underground Man\'s stage to play some new music. The first song he plays is from Toxic Apocalypse, a band from the Midwest. The Archers are playing some new stuff, and they\'ve just released a new song called Abyss. Then he plays some music from Kitty, a group from the Northern Ontario area. They\'ve been working on new stuff for a while now, so they\'re probably going to release a new album in the next couple of years. The other tracks are from other bands too, like Razor with Cross, Angels Apatrida, Aftermath, Cryptopsy, and Mindswell. All of these bands are coming together for a big tour in the fall. The next track is from a band called Demon Hunter, who was killed in battle.',NULL,NULL),(68387,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Forever Deaf - November 3, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 16:25:28',NULL,'So, here\'s what we\'ve got for you: music from the new albums Outside the Spiral, Cold Red, A Celebration I , Live in America , King Gizzard & the Lizard Wizard , and A Merciless Nation . And then some new music from a new band called Z-u-l-u. The band\'s name is Annelie Lee and they\'ve been together for a while. Annelie is a multi-instrumentalist and vocalist who\'s been making music since she was a teenager. Her band is called Zulu and they have a new album called I Do Tomorrow coming out soon. And they\'re going to play a bunch of new music. This isn\'t the music that we used to hear from this program, but it\'s cool.',NULL,NULL),(68416,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - November 3, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 16:24:05',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68426,124,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Planet Groove - November 3, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 10:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-13 15:44:46',NULL,'The show starts off with a description of the genre of music they\'re going to play. It\'s called \"Planet Groove of Your Funky Blues Doctor\" and it\'s about to get really interesting. The first show is going to be all about the \"Jurassic Park\" of music, but then the second show is all about \"Danger Sex Boss\" and \"Narusisa featuring BasilSilver and StephGoyer andMotorhead\" and the third show is about \"I\'ll be your sister baby from Overkill\" . The second show sounds like a mix of all of the same music, except you\'re singing along instead of playing along. The third show has \"Breeeeb Thunder Bay\" , and the fourth show is \"BeachBoys Long Promise Road\" ; the fifth show is called \"Kingdom Come\" and is about the band Robbie Robertson recently passed away from the band. The sixth show is a little more about the music, and this one is all \"Master versus Apprentice\" : people gotta move, triumph, and never surrender. The music ends with a shout out to Ed Video, the Guelph-based arts and culture hub. Get started, or advance your skills, with a year',NULL,NULL),(68427,123,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Thanks for Listening :) - November 3, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 15:33:10',NULL,'This is a special edition of the show where the guest introduces himself as \"Megan\" and explains that she will be with the hosts until the end of their show. She plays music and gives thanks for listening. They play music from the program and then she goes to her room to record. She tells us that she is a big fan of the bands Plague and Long Way Down and she remembers when she was younger and she was obsessed with them.',NULL,NULL),(68433,175,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/2eyrcj/November_2nd_2023_No_Man_s_Land70d29.mp3','2023-11-03 17:53:25',287962512,'2023-11-13 16:24:17',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68438,186,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ig5ezh/November_2nd_2023_Higher_Ground69fin.mp3','2023-11-03 17:58:59',287962512,'2023-11-13 15:13:54',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68439,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Democracy Now - November 3, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 15:04:10',NULL,'Meanwhile, the United States is spending money to defend Israel from Hamas\'s attacks. The House has passed a $14.3 bill to fund Israel\'s war effort. The Senate has approved a $106 bill to support Israel, Taiwan, and Ukraine. In the Middle East, the White House continues its refusal to allow a ceasefire in the fighting in Gaza. The vice president says the US will not create any conditions for the sale of weapons to Israel',NULL,NULL),(68440,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Volunteer Playlist - November 3, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 15:13:48',NULL,'Silence sounds is a community organization dedicated to preserving the magic of silent music. The organization needs your support to keep alive the arts in the community. We invite you to take the pledge of silence and donate $10 a month to keep music alive in the city.','fix',NULL),(68442,167,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/bjnqqb/November_3rd_2023_Funky_Fridaysafhho.mp3','2023-11-03 18:09:44',431961989,'2023-11-13 14:43:13',NULL,'Pete Whittier, host of \"Funky Fridays,\" has a special show for the listeners. He\'s going to dedicate it to Charles Stepney, a jazz and soul producer who was one of the pioneers of the psychedelic soul music of the mid-60s. Pete tells us all about Charles, his career, and why he\'s making this special show. Pete says he plays artists who are produced by the next arranger and composer. He always does a special feature on Charles. He puts together an hour and two hours of music and then he decides he wants to dedicate the whole show to Charles. Pete explains that Charles was the \"center of adventurous soul\" music coming out in the mid- 60s on \"chess records\" after the blues label had left. He was also the first to use the Moog synthesizer back in 1966.',NULL,NULL),(68451,126,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Viejoteca - November 3, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-03 20:06:54',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(68452,126,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Viejoteca - November 3, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 13:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-03 20:06:55',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(68462,257,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/whdsym/November_2_2023_Psychedelic_Stoner_Rock9o78i.mp3','2023-11-03 21:11:50',287962512,'2023-11-13 14:28:25',NULL,'The program begins with a description of the music that will be played for the hour. It begins with Ken Stauer introducing himself. He says that he hopes listeners will stay with him for the two hours and listen to the music. He tells listeners that he has prepared a playlist for them to listen to and that they can send a copy to him at Cient.FM or to Ken.stauer by e-mail at kenstauer@ciut.fm. Ken says that the music is from Astral Hand , Fuzz Sagrada , Sleeping Mountain , Killer Boogie , Hay Colossus , Greenleaf . The first track is called \"In a Sandbox Full Of Suns\" and the second is called Dina Sour. The third track is \"Way LuzziSombra\" by . . and the fourth is called Psychedelicide. The last song is \"Electric Rider\" by Greenleaf.',NULL,NULL),(68463,292,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/itwcpa/November_3_2023_The_Cool_Side_of_the_Pillowastlg.mp3','2023-11-03 21:09:37',287962512,'2023-11-13 13:28:05',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68468,170,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/g5nbnx/Ruby_Slippers_Nov_3_mp3_-_2023-10-30_346_PM6q4jt.mp3','2023-11-03 22:59:18',111378520,'2023-11-13 13:20:11',NULL,'Before the show starts, the Underground Man and his crew talk about how happy they are that they\'ve passed the Halloween candy craving test. He says that he hopes everyone had a good time and that everyone is safe after all. He goes on to say that he wants to start the show off with a band he\'s becoming more and more fond of lately. This band is Lowest Of The Low, the title of the band\'s latest album is Welcome To The Plunderdome, and the track name is Brave New Wold. The Underground Man says that this band sounds like his city. It\'s called Wild Bunch, and it\'s from Apollonio\'s new album Wild Bunch. And it\'sa classic from Mott The Hoople from his John Savage compilation from 1969-1971. Then there\'s Lowest of The Low. The name comes from the album Welcome to the Pplunderdome. And the track is called Brave New World, because the underground man just cannot let go of it. This is a band called Frenchie And The Punk. The title comes from Afternoon X, the album from earlier this year. He wants to remind everyone that this show has been posted on the Halloweenspot, CarolB on the',NULL,NULL),(68474,127,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/LiYghTE FM - November 3, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 13:07:40',NULL,'The DJ double-d character, who is also the host of the light FM station at the University of California, Los Angeles, begins this program by stating that the guy who works at the grocery store has no views and that he has heard that he is distant from his family and friends. He also says that he heard the guy is trying to change light FM from being the home of only 222% more hits to being home for the \"love revolution\" and that this is all part of the reason why he is so passionate about music. He goes on to say that every hour of light-FM is perfectly curated to roast chestnuts and every turn of the pan is perfectly timed to get the perfect temperature. The DJ says that his listeners already know these things. He says that light-fm used to be more budget and more producers exploring abroad, but that was the good side of everything. He then points out that nobody has ever defined the term \"light hit,\" and when they say \"light-hit\" it is also \"ill defined\" and \"undefinable. It is undefinable. He adds that a lot of the pop songs he listens to have a \"truly wild\" chorus. He further says that if listeners really listened to',NULL,NULL),(68475,128,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Walkuman Style - November 3, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 18:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-13 03:30:11',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68476,135,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Folk Roots Radio - November 3, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 03:23:59',NULL,'The show starts off with Helen Austin, a singer from Vancouver Island, and Paul Oten, a musician from Ohio, discussing their latest project, \"AMPM,\" a concept album. They talk about the project and its many aspects, including the songs that are based around the day in a person\'s life. The show ends with the latest releases from the artists on the show, including Bruce Coburn, Osanomu , Tara Spencer , Aspen Jacobson , Ben Kaplan , and more. Then it\'s back to Helen and Paul to talk about their new album, \"Oh It\'s you again,\" which is based on a day in life. Helen joins the show to tell us more about the album, and to thank her listeners for listening. She tells us that during the pandemic, she and her husband, as well as Paul and Jenny, were doing a weekly snack and chat.',NULL,NULL),(68477,1620,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Hellfire Radio - November 3, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 15:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-13 03:11:18',NULL,'The band introduces a new Swedish band called Cult of Luna. The band is psyched to be getting their Swedish fix on Hellfire. They\'re also psyched to play a song by a band that\'s not on the show: Dio\'s band, Guevore.',NULL,NULL),(68487,129,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Digital Statik - November 3, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 03:01:28',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68488,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Volunteer Playlist - November 3, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 02:52:37',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68498,216,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/3euiww/RAW11323.mp3','2023-11-04 02:18:21',287962512,'2023-11-13 02:44:11',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68499,132,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Global Rare Grooves - November 3, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 21:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-13 15:13:54',NULL,'The Global Rare Group starts off by talking about some of the music they\'ve just heard. They\'ll start with a bunch from Southeast Asia, and then they\'ll talk about the classics. Next up is a song from Ala Sounds. Then it\'s time for some more music. First up is an old classic from the 70s. Then we hear some new stuff. We\'ve heard a song by Choo Yan from the Panda Records album out of Singapore, and we\'ve also heard a new track from Black Classical Noise from Yousuf Day. And then we\'ll finish off the hour with a track from the Pharoah Sanders album, \"Pharahoah on India Navigation\" .','',NULL),(68500,1491,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Industry Tactics - November 3, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 02:22:03',NULL,'This is the first episode of the \"Industry Tactics\" podcast, and it\'s recorded in early 2022. It\'s a conversation between host Friendly Rich and Sebastian Corri, a musician who has been dubbed \"Corino\" by the press. In this conversation, Friendly Rich describes his first meeting with Sebastian, who is the leader of a Canadian political party called the \"Rhinoceros Party.\" In this interview, he describes Sebastian as a \"great ambassador of weird\" and says that he\'s grown to respect Sebastian\'s work. Sebastian is also psyched about his upcoming Carbon Dioxide test, which he\'ll perform live with Maladita, the girl he met in the bar when he first came to Montreal. The two also discuss Sebastian and his first time meeting Friendly Rich, which was at a bar in Montreal. Sebastian says that, at the time, the people at the bar called him by his stage name, but he doesn\'t speak English very well, so they just called him Corino. It turns out that the people in Montreal called him \"Sebastian Corri,\" but they didn\'t know what to say in English, so he calls himself \"Sebastian Corino.\" Friendly Rich says that Sebastian is a \"beautiful',NULL,NULL),(68510,1491,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Industry Tactics - November 3, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 23:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-13 02:11:47',NULL,'This is a really funny, funny, and depressing episode. It starts off with a guy named Sebastian Corino who\'s a big fan of the Canadian liberal party and a big supporter of socialism. He\'s also a big advocate of the idea of the free market. The guy\'s going on a tour in May and he\'s got a bunch of songs that he\'d like to play for the listeners. He also has some really funny political points about how he\'ll be very active in politics in the future. He wants to be active for democracy and not for socialism. We\'re going to turn this thing upside down and get into the 2025 elections. The next show is going to be a concert. It will be a totally different kind of music than what you\'ve come to expect from the CFR. There\'s no reason to miss this one. You can also lose. And that\'s the way it is.',NULL,NULL),(68511,1627,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Jitterbuggin - November 4, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 02:01:37',NULL,'This is a weird show, says Adrian, because it is not actually a Friday night show. It is actually a mid-week show, which means that he is in his home studio in Mississauga. He says that he\'s going to cut the music off as he goes. He\'s not going to be on the air as usual, but he\'ll try to come on as often as he can. He invites listeners to tune in as he does a little dance routine. He tells the listeners that he sets his time as midnight, not midnight where he is, because he is so up. He plays three different tracks, one each from a Canadian band and a soul gospel group. He also plays a triple header, meaning he plays three songs back-to-back. This means that no matter what time of day it is, he can play music. He adds that he has three tracks for each person, so they can listen to him while he does his thing.',NULL,NULL),(68549,1551,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ycb6k3/NOVEMBER2ND2023.mp3','2023-11-04 17:42:17',431961989,'2023-11-13 01:47:28',NULL,'In this week\'s show, David introduces the listeners to some new music from Roth Antic, which is based in Toronto. He also introduces Dim Kelly, a special guest DJ, who has a new EP called Pianoology, and he will also be playing tracks from that EP. Also on the docket for this week is a new album from Hercules, an album from Love Affair, and a new release from Vanity. The show closes with a mix from one of David\'s favorite producers, the Italian singer and songwriter, Dino Lenny.',NULL,NULL),(68550,136,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/A Dog’s Breakfast - November 4, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 01:36:31',NULL,'The group begins with a description of the music they are going to listen to. They are all going to be based in Toronto, and they are all singing Turkish. They have heard a lot of music at a dog\'d-breakfast, but this is the first time they\'ve heard something totally different. They\'re also going to hear a bunch of different kinds of music, but they\'re all coming from different parts of the world. They go from a Toronto based band called Minor Empire singing in Turkish, to a Vancouver based group called Pacifica singing in English, to another group called Rebetica singing in Greek. They also go to a Montreal based band named Land of Kush singing in Arabic, and a Toronto-based band named Sultans of String singing in Latin. The group ends with a music video for a snake. It\'s a nod to snakes, which isn\'t as common as spiders in the world , but it\'s still a good thing, and the group is going to go see it.',NULL,NULL),(68551,139,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Bel Araby with CAWA - November 4, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 01:23:29',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68552,138,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Sound Magic - November 4, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 01:17:13',NULL,'The program opens with a piece by a contemporary Czech composer, Victor Kalabis. He lived from 1922 to 2006. He married a harpsichordist, Susanna Ruzicakova, and he worked as a conductor and a producer for the state-run Czech Radio. The composer\'s opus 42 is a work for four movements. It is the work he wrote for his wife. He is aware of the influences of the composer, Bohuslavu, and has arranged for the composer to have Susanna perform it. The program concludes with a program of music from the late 20th century by another contemporary composer. This is the harpsichord concerto by Victor Kalabus. He lives until the late century, but unfortunately his health stops him from composing. The harpsichord concerto and his wife are played by the composer and the orchestra is also played. The music ends with a farewell program from Michael Dallashell. He says goodbye to his listeners and goes to work for another station.',NULL,NULL),(68553,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Caribbean Anthology - November 4, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 01:07:31',NULL,'The show starts off with an introduction to the music and then moves into the dance hall. Then it moves to the soca section and then back to the chart music section. The show was originally started by a guy named John Leacock who was a student at the university and a promoter. He used to have a CD collection of soca music that he would bring to the university for people to listen to. Leacock moved to real estate and decided to revive the music. He brought it back to live on the university station. Since that time, the show has been going strong.',NULL,NULL),(68554,138,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Sound Magic - November 4, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 00:58:34',NULL,'In this program, the UM continues his discussion of the music of Czech composer and friend of Vlst and Sukh, Joseph Vershteh. He relates that Verstuh wrote five symphonies, the fourth of which will be collected in a new edition in springtime. He also discusses the works of another friend of Sukh\'s, Vcevitslav Novak, a composer who has not had much success in the West. The UM also plays two pieces that he has never played before, the South Bohemian Suite and a tone poem.',NULL,NULL),(68555,138,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Sound Magic - November 4, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 00:49:14',NULL,'Sound Magic is the program of classical music concerts presented on the campus of the City University of New York. The program for this week\'s concert is a program of Czech music. This week\' composer is Josef Sukh, who was Dvorak\'s late son-in law and a major voice in the early 20th century. He is also known for his giant tom poem cycle, which he performed. The composer\'s Opus 25 is a fantasy piece. There is also a recording from the Buffalo Orchestra, conducted by Joanne Falera. The two orchestras are playing the fantasy piece on the Buffalo Philharmonic\'s recent album. The second program on the program is a Czech program. It is the time for the symphony at the later part of the program. This is a work by Paul Wernits, a composer who was famous in Vienna during Beethoven\'s time. He was well-respected. The symphony is published in 1797. It has four movements, an allegorymalto, adagio , a slow adogio, and then a vivace. The chamber orchestra of Patte Du Bice is conducting this symphony. It was the height of the classical style at the end.',NULL,NULL),(68556,1344,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Beautiful Druid - November 4, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 09:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-13 00:37:56',NULL,'In this short program, Alden Hadwen, the host of Beautiful Druid, introduces himself and introduces the program. He explains that the program will be a half-hour program, in which he will play songs and read poetry at the same time. He says that he will try and tell the audience who wrote the song, and that many of the songs will be performed by people who did not write the song but who appreciate it. The theme of the program is \"uplifting songs,\" and he starts by playing a song by Jesse Winchester called Doulalé. He dedicates the song to Doulalé\'s \"wonderful listener,\" whom he calls \"Doulalé.\" After this, he plays a steel drum band called \"Steel Drum Beach Party.\" He then plays a song called \"The Secret of Life,\" which was written by a woman named Gretchen Peters. After that he plays \"All That Is,\" a song written by Garnet Rogers. Then he plays another song by Holly Cole, \"I Can See Clearly,\" which she sings with a trio. He also plays George Strait\'s song, \"In the Air Again,\" which he recorded in 1999.',NULL,NULL),(68566,141,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Alternativa Latinoamericana - November 4, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-05 00:07:08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(68567,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Caribbean Anthology - November 4, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 00:24:44',NULL,'The Underground Man explains that he is trying to keep the whole thing going, but that he also wants people to be aware that they are not alone and that they can find help if they need it. He says that there is no way to do it and that it is very difficult, but he urges people to get together and find out what they can do to help themselves.',NULL,NULL),(68569,171,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/hdzg6a/phil_s_inn_nov_4_237i2lv.mp3','2023-11-05 00:32:05',287962512,'2023-11-13 00:15:33',NULL,'The group goes to the fall fair, where they listen to a variety of different acts. The first act is the band Luther Dickinson and his band the Collaborators, who perform an old spiritual song called \"Bula Land\" which is a metaphor for \"heaven.\" The second act is Alison Russell and her band the All Stars, the Black Crows, who play a song originally written by Billy J Kramer called \"Dakotas, Trains, and Planes.\" The third act is The Box Tops from Memphis, TN who perform a song by Billy Chilton called \"The Box Tops.\"',NULL,NULL),(68578,197,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/jie9ht/phil_s_inn_nov_4_23723co.mp3','2023-11-05 00:48:51',287962512,'2023-11-13 00:02:28',NULL,'In a rare interview, a Boston-based musician opens up about his travels and the music he has been listening to. He tells how he loves New England and how he came to be in the audience at a fall fair in Hamilton, Ontario. He explains that he is in the middle of a conversation with a Canadian company when he hears the music of Luther Dickinson and Allison Russell. They are both playing an old spiritual song called \"Bula Land,\" which is a metaphor of heaven. The song was originally written by Billy J, who performed it in the Dakota Mountains. The two artists perform the song together.',NULL,NULL),(68579,141,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Alternativa Latinoamericana - November 4, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 19:00:00',0,'2023-11-05 02:07:20',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(68652,142,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Tiempo de Mujeres - November 4, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-05 19:07:13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(68653,143,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Mach Vibe Radio - November 4, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-12 23:50:12',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68654,143,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Mach Vibe Radio - November 4, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-12 23:42:55',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68655,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/Visions fugitives - November 5, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-12 23:34:35',NULL,'The show is called \"Git\'in\' Jean Fujitiv\" and it\'s hosted by Christopher Curry and Fangwei. Each week, Fangwei and Curry co-host a show. This week, the show is titled \"The Serpent-Fire,\" and it is inspired by the story of the serpent in the Bible, which tempts Eve to eat forbidden fruit. It\'s a work that doesn\'t quite go well with the story, but that\'s OK because the serpent is better than the apple in the story. So, this week, Curry wants to play a piece called \"Opus 13,\" which is a number associated with unlucky numbers. The reason for the unlucky number is that there are 13 people in the Last Supper, and one of them was a traitor, so the unlucky thing is that the number 13 is associated with bad luck. But, the good news is that Sunday is \"Sunday the 13th\" of November, which means that it\'ll just be a bunch of people who are Triska decafies. If you want to play your own piece of music, you can do so. But this is not a work of yours, says Curry, because he\'s not breaking',NULL,NULL),(68656,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/Visions fugitives - November 5, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-12 23:24:01',NULL,'The Christopher Curry and Fangwei co-host a music show called \"Visions of Fugitives.\" It\'s a sort of music-as-codicil show, where one of the co-hosts plays a piece and the other plays another piece. One week they\'ll play a bunch of music and the next week they can respond to the first piece they heard with their own selections. The show is sort of like a game of Who\'s Who in the music world. The two of them pick a song cycle and then they play the song that they heard the week before. The song cycle is called \"United Fruit Company.\" It was written by a Greek composer named Mikis Teodolians. It was one of many pieces written by Neruda that were set to music during the period of military rule in Greece from 1967 to 1974.',NULL,NULL),(68657,146,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/The Kookoo Bananas Variety Hour - November 5, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-08 14:17:16',NULL,'We start off this new episode with a song about robots. It\'s called \"Computers! Robots have Computers inside them basically two different things though.\" The first song is from Disney World. It was written by a group called the Sherman Brothers. They wrote songs for all the Disney theme parks. The song is called \"Everything Is Awesome\" and it\'s one of the most popular songs of all time. The second song that we\'re going to hear is a song by a guy called \"Jerry Paper\" . The guy\'s got a song called \"Fuzzy Logic\" , which is about being able to create something in the world that isn\'t just a yes or no. The world is like this. The cover of Jerry Paper\'s album is awesome. We\'ll start this song off with \"Lampan Fuzzy Logic,\" which sounds like a talking robot. It sounds like the voice of a German-speaking robot. Jerry Paper has a song for the kids called \"Jingles,\" which is also about a robot. The idea of a robot taking over the whole world is so awesome that it was actually the first song on the radio. It came from a game called \"Um Jamma Lamm','Rowan shares his favorite songs from Disney World, the Jungle Book, and a video game. Rowan also shares a song about how computers will take over the world. The song is called Fuzzy Logic and was written by the Sherman Brothers who also wrote songs for Disney.','The Magician’s Favorite Songs From Disney World, the Jungle Book, and Video Games '),(68658,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/The Underground - November 5, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-12 22:14:07',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68659,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/The Underground - November 5, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 9