:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 11:00:53',NULL,'The opening track of this week\'s Turo Island Sound Show is a mix of experimental music from around the world. It is a mixture of progressive fusion, alternative styles, and other discoveries. The narrator says he would like to pay respect to local indigenous communities and recognize that the music is heard across treaty territories. He also acknowledges that many of the music styles originated from Black culture, and he thanks the Black community for their contribution to alternative music. The first track of the week is a song by the singer-songwriter of the Czech Republic, Golden State. She has just released an album on Bandcamp. The second track is an electropop track by the artist from Vancouver, Her Head Is a House. The third track is a grime track by Beverly Glenn and his album Ones Ahead. The fourth track is by Helios Kenneth, an ambient project. The fifth track is one by Lawrence Ann from Montreal. The sixth track is called Vites, an experimental track on an album called Ornament Sea',NULL,'The Turo Island Sound Show: A mix of experimental music from around the world (11 minute read)'),(68827,83,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/to know the land - November 6, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 10:49:33',NULL,'The narrator says he grew up in the area of the Chesapeake Bay and the Appalachian Mountains. He describes the region as a \"middle zone\" where there are \"a lot of interesting geologically speaking, but also we sit in the middle zone\" . The narrator tells us that he has always been fascinated by faraway places, but that he prefers to stay at home and study the land. He says that the more he studies, the deeper he gets into the subject, and the more questions he has about it. The more he wants to know about someone, the more depth he wants in the relationship.',NULL,'The narrator\'s favorite place to study is the Chesapeake Bay '),(68828,82,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Big Sis Radio - November 6, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 10:36:53',NULL,'Big Sis Radio plays a set of songs by the Balutos. The first song is called \"Aligned by theBlaze Baluto\" and it\'s off of their latest album \"What\'s On your Mind\". The second song is \"Electric Spital Attack\". The third song is a cover of a song called \"You, you you, you\" by the same band.',NULL,'Big Sis Radio plays the Balutos\' latest album '),(68838,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Blues Around the Block - November 6, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 10:20:33',NULL,'Mac Dee is the host of the latest edition of the weekly program, \"Blues Around the Block\" on CFRU\'s 93.3 FM. The music is described in the program\'s title, \"I\'m Old Enough to Know Better.\" He also provides a link to past editions of the program, which can be streamed or downloaded from the CFRU archives. Mac Dee also introduces himself as Mac D, a 41-year-old father of two. He explains that he has a business degree and loves to tell jokes.',NULL,'Mac Dee is the host of CFRU\'s 93.3 FM Blues Around the Block '),(68839,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Blues Around the Block - November 6, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 10:09:43',NULL,'Mac Dee welcomes listeners to his show, \"Blues Around the Block.\" He tells them that they can watch the show on CFRU.org or by downloading it from the university\'s website. Mac Dee also tells listeners that if they enjoyed the show, they can reach him by email at macd@cfr.ca. He also tells them to keep the show locked on the university for more blues. Mac D closes the show with a song by the \"glamour puss band\" Live at Shadackd. If you\'re in the middle of a crisis or have a mental health issue, you can get help from a toll-free helpline, 1-866-531.',NULL,'Listen to Mac Dee\'s show, \"Blues Around the Block,\" on CFRU.org '),(68848,86,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/The Deep House Project - November 6, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 09:58:11',NULL,'The Underground DJ\'s talk about their upcoming show. They\'re playing a mix of tracks that are going to be featured in their upcoming PSA, which is coming up on September 24th at the Tri City Synth Society\'s open mic night. The Underground DJs are psyched to be playing at the upcoming PSA. They invite you to check them out on Facebook or on X, since they\'ll be posting the music of the show there. Back to the USSR is the first thing that comes to mind. It starts off by saying that they\'ve been listening to a local FM station right now, and they\'re doing a lot of work for the homeless. They want to help the Canadian Alliance end homelessness. They also want to do some work for a local charity called Spelled D\'I-Y\'O\'D.',NULL,'The Underground DJs are psyched to be playing at the Tri City Synth Society’s open mic night '),(68849,85,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Ripcord Radio - November 6, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 09:48:28',NULL,'The band\'s studio album, \"Burnham wits and Liberation Fly,\" was originally released in 1993 on only vinyl, but the original artwork was not the correct one. The band tried to correct the mistake, but it was too late. The record label, \"temporary residence limited,\" issued a new limited edition of the album, and the band had to perform the original release live. The other albums released in this time period include \"Naked Ray Gun With Home of the Brave,\" \"Lamb Faucet With Cut Larry,\" \"Shocked Out,\" \"Shot Maker With Two Left Standing,\" \"Cray Crayon Club,\" \"A Moment In Time 1993 to 1996,\" and \"City Babies Revenge,\" which were all released back when they were known as charged.',NULL,'The band was forced to reissue their 1993 studio album after it was mistakenly released on vinyl '),(68857,87,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Back in the USSR - November 6, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 09:36:40',NULL,'The show opens with a description of the program and its purpose. The program is dedicated to the plight of the people of the Occupied Territories, particularly the people in Gaza. Seigfried, the host, says that his shows have been dedicated to this cause for the past few weeks. He explains that there is still no ceasefire in the conflict, despite the fact that the entire world calls for one. The show has been attended by hundreds of thousands of the world\'s citizens, who have gathered in cities all over the world to demand a cease-fire. As they have, however, he says, they have not been able to get into the personal toll of the conflict. He has not gotten into the human side of the story. He says that he is going to play an excerpt from an interview he had with a visiting professor named Hada Ad-jeal, who lost many of her family members in the war. She is a third generation refugee from Beit-Dal, a village in the south of the Gaza Strip. Her family was supposed to live in the safe area in southern Gaza in the summer of 2016, but last week, the bombs went off without warning. Hada and her daughter, Nora, explain that',NULL,'The Host of \'Seigfried\': The World\'s Most Inspiring Show on the Crisis in Gaza'),(68858,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Rainbow Country - November 7, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 09:24:21',NULL,'This program is part of a three-part episode of Rainbow Country, a weekly radio show hosted by Mark Tara that airs on 12 different Canadian radio stations. In this program, the program is described as a \"little gay radio show\" that is \"working to give voice\" to the \"LGBT community and beyond\" and is produced by and hosted by \"Barbie Q\" and \"the P-Girl\" . The show airs every day on CIUT FM, which is the largest public radio station in Canada. Rainbow Country is a \"nationally syndicated\" gay-owned and operated show, a \"number one LGBT podcast\" and a \"gay and lesbian chart\" on \"Podomatic.com\" and on \"Feedspot.com.\" The show is also a \"one-stop shop\" for information about the various Canadian film festivals, including the 48th. The first part of the program features three Canadian films: \"Solo,\" \"Summer Camp,\" and \"The Short Bloom.\" In the second part, the show features three music and two music videos from the LGBTQ community, all of which are produced on \"this episode\" of the show. In the third part, \"Journey 377,\" the show is described',NULL,'This is a \"little gay radio show\" that is \"working to give voice\" to the \"LGBT community and beyond\" '),(68863,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Rainbow Country - November 7, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 08:59:47',NULL,'Marc Tara, the creator of the popular music podcast, \"Rainbow Country,\" introduces himself and his show. He\'s a musician, songwriter, and producer who\'s been working in the music business for over 20 years. He has a big voice in the business, and he\'s got a lot to say in this one. He describes himself as \"an artist, a songwriter, a producer, and a musician.\" He also says that he wants to be a part of the business because he thinks it\'s important to have a place to express his feelings and ideas. He hopes listeners will stick around and listen to his music. He also wants to thank them for their support and says he hopes they\'ll all believe in him. Finally, he asks them to take him out for one of his original tracks.',NULL,'The creator of the popular music podcast, \"Rainbow Country,\" tells us how he wants to be a part of the'),(68877,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/CFRU Playlist - November 7, 2023 at 06:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 06:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 08:50:29',NULL,'The show\'s narrator introduces the narrator, a Philadelphia-based musician and field recording artist. He explains that he is a member of a band called Hotel, which also includes a group called Mortensage, and he lives in Philadelphia. The narrator describes the region of the U.S. as being in the middle of the country, between the northeast and the southeast. He describes the landscape as \"quite an interesting confluence\" of geological, historical, and climate elements. He says that the region is so varied that he will never tire of exploring it.',NULL,'The Mid-Atlantic: The U.S. in the Mid-Century '),(68887,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - November 7, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 08:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-10 08:37:29',NULL,'This is the first of a series of songs that Thomas King will perform in Guelph and throughout the rest of the province. The first song is titled \"Morning Soul Shake-up\" and it is a celebration of the \"morning soul\" and \"rare soul\" that characterize the sounds of the day. The song begins by introducing the listener to Thomas King who is the host of a popular morning show on CFRU. The show airs every day of the week and mixes soul music with funk. The theme of the song is \"be good or not\" and Thomas King says that he is not a man and that this is the time to \"fire me up\"',NULL,'\'Morning Soul Shake-Up\' is Thomas King\'s first song to celebrate the sound of the day '),(68897,2653,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Solipsistic Retreat - November 7, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 08:28:35',NULL,'The guys talk about the McCrackens, a band from New York City that\'s one of the best-selling indie acts of all-time. The band\'s first album, Tommy the Chicken from Gob, was actually released in the same year as Tommy\'s debut album, What Came First, which was a huge hit. The guys agree that it\'s awesome that guitarists can play the drums and that drummers can understand how to play the other instruments. The group\'s drummer, Spot, is a dog, which means he\'s the better drummer. So, listen to the band. If you like the band, then you can listen to them, even if you hate them. But if you like them, you can\'t just listen to their music. You have to support them through your music. Sounds like a good idea, right? According to the Canadian Medical Association, one in eight people will die without a living donor of their own. So if you want to save someone\'s life, you\'ve got to register. You can become a donor by going to BeAdonor.ca.',NULL,'How to become a living donor in Canada (13 minute read)'),(68898,2653,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Solipsistic Retreat - November 7, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 08:19:41',NULL,'The boys are back from their trip to their friends and family and they\'re listening to a program called \"Solipsistic Retreat\" on CFRU 93.2. They\'re talking about a band called Rec Center and there\'s also a solo band called the Ramones. Tommy Ramone is one of the original members of the band, and he\'s been making music since the \'80s. The boys say they\'ve listened to a lot of music, including the Ramones, and they all have a favorite Ramone. One of the boys says he was told the Ramones were like Green Day, but he couldn\'t listen to them because he was too young to understand how seriously they took their music. He says he cried when he heard the Ramones say he cried and he cried, but eventually he realized that the joke was his friends because the Ramones knew how they sounded, and it was really funny. The brothers decide to follow the Ramones\' lead and listen to people who aren\'t like them. They decide to sing to someone who isn\'t their own caricature. And then they decide to listen to someone they like.',NULL,'The Ramones Are Like Green Day, And They\'re Laughing (11 minute read)'),(68908,90,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Bridging The Social Distance - November 7, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 08:09:24',NULL,'The narrator introduces us to Jenny Mitchell, a long-time CFR listener who is currently living at Riverside Glen. She\'s 92 years old and a widow with five children who have all died of breast cancer. She has 11 grandchildren and eight great-grandchildren, all of whom are boys. One of her great-grandchildren is four years old. She says her birthday is coming up soon, and she doesn\'t know when it will be. She plans to have a party for her family, but no one has come up with a plan. She also says that she\'s planning to rent a hall and invite everyone over for a party. She wants a magician to play music for half-an-hour, and hopes that everyone will enjoy it.',NULL,'Jenny Mitchell, a 92-year-old CFR listener, is planning a birthday party for her family '),(68909,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Democracy Now - November 7, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 11:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-10 07:58:01',NULL,'The war in the Gaza continues to escalate, and the United Nations reports that at least 10,000 people have been killed and over 4,000 children have been injured. Israel has ordered the evacuation of a children\'s hospital in the city of Rafah. The hospital is being used as a staging ground for Israel\'s ground offensives. The Israeli military has admitted that it accidentally struck a group of ambulances outside the Al-Shifah Hospital last week, killing 15 people and wounding dozens of others. The patient, a man named Hanid Abi Hawim Saad, tells how he narrowly survived last week\'s attack. He says that he was on his way to Egypt when the ambulance came under fire, killing the passengers in the ambulance and forcing them to return to the hospital. The man\'s injuries include a fractured skull, a dislocated shoulder, and a broken head. Israel will not comply with international calls for an immediate cease-fire, however, because it does not want to release its prisoners.',NULL,'Israel orders evacuation of children\'s hospital in Gaza, says man who survived last week\'s deadly attack '),(68912,155,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/a5epfk/DrMouth_CIUTshow_nov7_2023_fullshow.mp3','2023-11-07 19:52:21',287261888,'2023-11-10 07:46:05',NULL,'Dr. Mouth opens the show with a \"rock and roll lunch party\" , which he describes as a \"two hours of solid rock and roll for you\" . The first song is from the new album by Neil Young called \"Barn.\" The second song is a \"laid out mellow almost blues thing happening\" from Crazy Horse. The third song is \"Pleasant Dreams\" from the \"Reconstruction de Blanc\" album by the Ramones. The fourth song is one of the most famous songs in the entire Marvel Cinematic Universe , \"Spider-Man versus the Fly.\" The fifth track is from \"Foot in Cold Water\" by the Foot in the Cold Water.',NULL,'Dr. Mouth opens the show with a \"rock and roll lunch party\" '),(68920,125,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Power Up! with Electrified Voltage - November 7, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 02:12:02',NULL,'This program opens with a description of the songs on the program. The songs are listed alphabetically. The first song is from Nigeria, the second is from Brazil, the third is from Germany, the fourth is from Ivory Knight, the fifth is from New Zealand, the sixth is from Colombia, the seventh is from Alistair James, the eighth is from Natalia, the ninth is from The Cranberries, the tenth is from Lip Select, the eleventh is from Future Memories, the twelfth is from Gorilla Systems, the thirteenth is from Irish band The Chieftains, and the fourteenth is from Machiana.',NULL,'The Songs of the World (13 minute audio program), Part 1 (22 minute video)'),(68921,1783,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Under the Needle - November 7, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 13:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-10 01:59:12',NULL,'On this show, we\'re introduced to the desert rock band TamaCrest, who come from France, Mali, and Niger. They\'re all from the same place: the Sahara. The band\'s singer, Usman, lives everywhere in the world because he\'s a \"bio\" . But generally he walks somewhere north of Algeria and south of Mali. They have a new album out called Tamotate on Glitterbeat, and they\'re influenced by some of the most famous acts in the music world, like Dire Straits and Pink Floyd. They also wrote a song about a remote island in Japan, which they played on this show. This is the first time we\'ve heard the songs from this album, so we\'ll have to wait until next week to hear more. Also, check out the 50 Years of Hip-Hop on KEXP podcast. You can listen to this show wherever you listen, and be sure to watch the video. This program is made possible by the Corporation For Public Broadcasting. KEXP is a public station that is owned and operated by the University of California, Berkeley. The University has a community outreach team that works to promote local events and festivals. They need people to help out',NULL,'KEXP’s 50 Years of Hip-Hop (Sponsor)'),(68931,217,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/rucb2v/CIUTOct31.mp3','2023-11-07 21:57:02',143961989,'2023-11-10 01:46:33',NULL,'This is the second part of David James\'s creepy Halloween show, \"The Creepy Halloween Hootenanny Part 2.\" It\'s an all-new set that includes \"House of Hunt,\" \"Amazing Crowns,\" \"Southern Culturana,\" \"Deja Vuja,\" and \"alleydukes.\" In this second part, David introduces the audience to the various characters in the show and explains the concept of the blue eyes, which are the eyes of a man\'s face. This is a reference to the \"blue match\" in the English language that refers to the blue color of a person\'s eyes, as opposed to the yellow color of an English man\'S face. He also describes the show\'s theme, \"Christmas spirits,\" as a way of \"stirring all creatures.\"',NULL,'The Creepy Halloween Hootenanny Part 2 (Sponsor)'),(68932,1453,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Silver Screen Dream Machine - November 7, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 01:33:55',NULL,'The show starts off with a musical comedy trio called The Arrogant worms from their 2002 concert film Three worms in an Orchestra. It\'s an orchestral version of \"The Last Saskatchewan Pirate,\" which is about a pirate captain who stole fertilizer from a ship in the Norwegian harbor. The song is a bit of a tongue-in-cheek take on life. The band also makes a surprise appearance in the animated film \"Hans Zimmer,\" which was released in the mid-1990s. On October 28 th , the world lost Matthew Perry who played the role of \"Chandler Bing\" on the long running sitcom Friends from 1994 until its end in 2004. He died suddenly in his tub. The show then turns to the 2000 crime comedy Oz Gets A Surprise, which stars Matthew Perry as Oz-Ozzina alongside Bruce Willis. The score is by Randy Edelman. Then we hear the opening credits of \"Almost Heroes,\" a 1998 film directed by Chris Farley and starring Matthew Perry and Chris Vanston as explorers in the 1800\'s. And then we hear a mix of the soundtrack to \"Friends,\" the sitcom which has made Matthew Perry famous. And finally, the show closes with a set of covers of four songs by Van Parks. The',NULL,'The Last Saskatchewan Pirate, The Arrogant Worms, and Matthew Perry\'s Death in a Tub '),(68933,3033,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/A Multilingual Affair - November 7, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 01:17:04',NULL,'The foursome of Cosmovermo, HIM57, and Piers Ulvit bring their unique sound to the concert. The show begins with an introduction by A 777, who explains that he was talking with a friend about the world of music when he realized that the words he was using were inspirational. He plans to use the words to inspire others to pursue their dreams.',NULL,'A 777, Cosmovermo, HIM57, and Piers Ulvit Bring Their Sound to a Concert '),(68943,91,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Tuesday at 5 - November 7, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 17:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-10 00:53:47',NULL,'On Remembrance Day, the show opens with a song about love changing. The song is about a woman who tells her lover that she no longer loves him. The tune is from an album by William Prince called \"Stand in the Joy\" and it\'s a collection of six songs. Also included is a song by Ken Dunn called \"Shifting Sand\" and a song called \"Blurry Days\" from Patrick Creif\'s album \"When You Miss Someone.\" The song by Sia is about madness. The show ends with a long song about the importance of Remembrance Day. This year, the Remembrance Day is on Saturday, so the show chooses songs that speak to him to remember. The first song is from a singer named Lorena McKeinnett who released an album called \"Elemental\" in 1985. The second song is by Douglas Campbell who recited a poem by William Blake called \"Lullaby.\" And the third song is a tune by the Kingston trio who recorded \"Where Have All the Flowers Gone\" in 1961. The fourth song is an Elton John song about \"Blueberry Hill.\" The show\'s not very eventful. The kids had four visits to trick or treat, and the house chores were very limited. The only activity',NULL,'The Remembrance Day Show Is a Must-See for All Veterans (13 minute read)'),(68944,1455,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Down the Rabbit Hole - November 7, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 00:42:37',NULL,'The Underground Man takes us back to his apartment and tells us that he\'s had a great day. He\'s been talking to a friend about art and music, and he thinks it\'s really cool. He also says that sometimes small talk can be a good thing, because sometimes you need to talk to other people about things that you\'re interested in. He plays a song by Wisp