uity and community food. They discuss the importance of water to society and how it can be used to benefit people. Lewis is a graduate student in food science at the university. He and Hannah May, a fellow student, are discussing water and how nutrients end up in the Great Lakes.',NULL,'The World\'s Most Influential Genocide Specialist (13 minute read)'),(69042,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/08/Democracy Now - November 8, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-08 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-09 21:15:48',NULL,'The House of Representatives votes to censure a member of Congress for criticizing Israel\'s recent war in the occupied territories, including the killing of civilians in the Gaza Strip. The speaker of the House calls for a ceasefire, but a survivor of the Second World War tells us that she feels compassion for the suffering of the people in the besieged territory. An aerial bombardment continues, and thousands of people have fled the area. A resident of the area says that the Israeli strikes are a \"genocide,\" and that no one cares about them. A doctor from Doctors Without Borders mourns the death of a colleague who was killed in the attack on the Al-Shati refugee camp in Israel. In Jerusalem, mourners gather to mark a month since the attack by Hamas. They demand the release of the 240 hostages still held by the family of the late Hannah Katzmann. She was one of the first people to protest against the government before the attack.',NULL,'The House of Representatives censures a member of Congress for criticizing Israel’s war in the occupied territories '),(69045,174,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ds33rb/November_8_2023_Global_Rhythms6dvg4.mp3','2023-11-08 19:06:33',431961989,'2023-11-09 21:01:40',NULL,'Ken Stowar introduces the program, which is a combination of music, news, and conversation. The program is hosted by Ken and produced by Ken. The first program is called \"Global Rhythms\" and is a mix of music and news. The second program is \