roup meets to discuss the new budget. They\'re planning to make some decisions about the budget, but they\'re also planning to take a moment to reflect on their privilege to live in a city built on rich indigenous history. The first thing the group is going to do is to think about how they\'ll care for the land, people, and generations to come in the future. First things first: Scott Stewart, the city\'s chief administrative officer, is here to help them understand the budget. The budget is the first of two Mayor\'s budgets, covering 2024 through 2027. Scott Stewart is an expert on the process, and he\'ll explain everything to the group. They can ask questions, but Scott will be the one to answer them. Scott explains that it\'s important to remember that the first budget is for a mayor, and the second budget is a multi-year plan that covers 2024 to 2027',NULL,NULL),(69287,206,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/2ghssi/November_11th_2023_The_Minx_Sessions7zup1.mp3','2023-11-13 18:09:34',287962512,'2023-11-13 19:56:37',NULL,'This is a short program from the music show on community radio station CIUT 99.5. It\'s called the \"Mink Sessions\" and it\'s hosted by David. He\'s a regular on the show and he\'s always been a big fan of independent artists. David introduces the new artist Cousin, who\'s from Australia and is coming out with a new album called \"Home Soon,\" which will be released later this year. The show starts out with an old favorite, Etienne De Cressy.',NULL,NULL),(69288,247,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/usq8fv/November_11th_2023_Calling_All_Bluesaipas.mp3','2023-11-13 18:11:33',143961989,'2023-11-13 19:46:25',NULL,'The program opens with a look back at the past month\'s releases. It seems that this is a very good time to release some new music. First up is Kingfish Ingram, who won a Grammy for his work on the recently released Chris Stone album. Next up is Big Krit who is releasing a remix album of a song that he wrote called \"Blues Meets Rap.\" The remi