volved with the prophecy for 20 years, but he has wanted to continue it for a while because he wants to do more shows at Cool London, where he works. So he decided to take over the show. He wants to bring in the current crew, including himself, Polaris, and Mr. Brown, and he says that the prophecy means something to him. He explains that the original track was by Fabian, but that\'s when the crew chose the name for it.\n\nThe whole idea was that some people live in the future. In other words, some people are living for the future, and the music is futuristic. The prophecy was like a dream for Marcus Visionary when he was a young DJ in the underground.',NULL,NULL),(69311,179,'https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/audio/grooveconceptradio.mp3','2023-11-14 21:02:09',0,'2023-11-16 09:33:18','2023-11-14 21:05:26','',NULL,NULL),(69312,181,'https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/audio/reggaeriddims.mp3','2023-11-14 20:58:41',0,'2023-11-16 09:20:58','2023-11-14 21:05:28','In this program, Roots talks about the various events taking place in the city. He tells us that they\'re celebrating 15 years of being a community station. He also tells listeners that the funding for the station starts soon. They\'re also going to be putting on a fund-raising show on November 18th. He introduces the new artist named Charlie music. Charlie, as he\'s called, is a member of the band K. He says he wants to thank K for supporting him tonight.',NULL,NULL),(69313,188,'https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/audio/masterplan.mp3','2023-11-14 20:58:33',0,'2023-11-16 09:06:27','2023-11-14 21:05:47','The show starts with a shout-out to the listeners at the station who have been supporting the show all these years. They\'re also giving thanks to all the DJs who played on the show and to the people who have supported the show in the past. The show ends with a salute to everyone who has been keeping the station going for 30 years. The listeners are asked to tune in to the show on November 11th for the \"Old School Pick of the Week\" and the \"Freddy with cuckoo clocking\"',NULL,NULL),(69314,190,'https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/audio/thebassmentsessions.mp3','2023-11-14 21:01:23',0,'2023-11-16 08:53:18','2023-11-14 21:05:50','',NULL,NULL),(69315,194,'https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/audio/radioboogie.mp3','2023-11-14 21:04:03',0,'2023-11-16 08:44:00','2023-11-14 21:05:54','The program opens with the announcement that the next show will be a celebration of the release of a new record by Sylvia Tyson, an artist who is 70 years old and has released a collection of songs that reflect on her life. The program then discusses the other artists who have released new albums in the past few months. The first artist is Connie Calder, who will be performing at the Acoustic Harvest folk club on the 18 th . The second artist is Alice Girard, who has released an album that is reflective of her own life.',NULL,NULL),(69316,193,'https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/audio/classicalunderground.mp3','2023-11-14 21:04:11',0,'2023-11-14 21:05:56','2023-11-14 21:05:56',NULL,NULL,NULL),(69317,125,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/14/Power Up! with Electrified Voltage - November 14, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-14 14:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-16 08:26:24','2023-11-14 21:07:20','This week on the Power Up program, the listeners are treated to some of the best music from Canada, Australia, the Philippines, Norway, and the U.S. We start off by hearing a song from Chester, then we hear a song called \"Fire\" from the Australian band Wild Ride, then a song by Celia Carlson, then from the Norwegians we hear \"I Don\'t care if you\'re beautiful\" from her \"Beauty for the Blind\" EP, and finally from the Filipinos we hear another song by the band Tribe. The song is called \"The Way you Make Me Feel.\" Then we hear the song \"Where it Begins\" from \"Voodoo Tribe.\n\n\" Finally, we hear Adrian Raso\'s song \"Revenge of Ganesh,\" which is a long piece that\'s been recorded over the past 20 years. This is from his debut album SuperSonic Music Man, which was released in 1999. Now we hear Atilane\'s songs, starting with \"Telegramma,\" from her latest EP MeidoEmor Iveda, then \"The Doves,\" an English band that was active from 1998-2010.',NULL,NULL),(69318,1783,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/14/Under the Needle - November 14, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-14 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-16 08:13:00','2023-11-14 21:08:03','The show is called \"Live on KEXP\" and it\'ll be the second time it\'s been called that. It\'s this time, we\'re talking about a band called \"Spirit Award.\" They\'re a band that\'s making a lot of noise in the Seattle music scene. The band\'s lead singer, Daniel Lyon, is a singer-guitarist, songwriter, and producer. He\'s also a member of the band, and they\'re releasing their latest album, \"The Fear,\" on Share It. The first album was called \"Never Ending\" because it took so long to finish. The second album was a little different, though, called \"The Lunatic House,\" because it wasn\'t going to be as depressing as the first one.\n\nIt was more like a \"release of pent up emotion and energy\" . KEXP\'s DJ, Cheryl Waters, asks about the new album. The new album is like a release, and it feels like you\'ve let the past go, and you\'re opening new doors and new opportunities. He tells her that the new record is kind of like letting it come and go, like he has a little bit of a trance-',NULL,NULL),(69319,1453,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/14/Silver Screen Dream Machine - November 14, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-14 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-16 03:44:41','2023-11-14 23:07:57','The show opens with a tribute to Canadian music icon Robbie Robertson. He was one of Martin Scorsese\'s most trusted collaborators, and he composed the music for many of his films. The show starts off with a piece from his score for the upcoming film, Killers Of The Flower Moon.\n\nIt is called \"From the Soundtrack To