hat they cannot liberate their land, that the war should be short- and decisive, and that they should not worry about their revolution. Both the Israelis and the Arabs sent secret police to arrest their commanders. All governments feared the revolution',NULL,NULL),(69348,97,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Wild Combination - November 16, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 09:02:38','2023-11-16 09:06:37','EdVideo is a local organization that offers a variety of creative workshops and educational opportunities for people of all ages. The organization is open to all levels of creative expression. EdVideo\'s goal is to provide a place for people to learn, create, and display their work.',NULL,NULL),(69349,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - November 16, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 08:51:01','2023-11-16 15:06:24','',NULL,NULL),(69350,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Here Today - November 16, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 07:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 08:43:22','2023-11-16 15:06:45','Aaron Badgley, host of the popular CFRU 96.3FM show, takes us back to the present to tell us about some of the latest music. First, he tells us that Paul Manchin has released a new album, Master, which contains some of his most popular songs. Then he brings us up to speed on the latest news from the music scene. He gives us a rundown of all the latest releases, including a song by the Beatles, a new song by Church of Trees, and an update on the work of Deborah Fialkov.',NULL,NULL),(69351,111,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Tales from the Bridge - November 16, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 08:31:13','2023-11-16 17:06:36','The guys get a bunch of new stuff to discuss, and this time, they\'re talking about a book. This one\'s called \"The Art of Living in Space.\" And it\'s all about living inside of an asteroid, which is a really popular space-colonization idea in science fiction, according to the guys. But there\'s another guy who\'s done some research on this, and he\'s written a paper showing how to do it in 12 years, which makes the guys super excited. The whole thing sounds like a good idea, but it\'ll take a lot of hard work and a lot more than that, because you need to build a huge, expensive space station to get to the moon.',NULL,NULL),(69352,112,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/FoodFarm Talk - November 16, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 10:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 08:21:00','2023-11-16 17:06:36','This episode of Behind the Aroma is all about supporting local farmers, and this is a big part of why we do it. We\'re supporting the people who are doing the \"itty gritty work\" behind the scenes, not just the \"people here\" or the \"corporations\" who are buying the original product.\n\nWe talk about Balzac\'s three different beans, one of which supports the Atwood blend. The other two beans support women\'s farmers in particular, and Balzac has been working with them to make sure that they sell all of their products to support them. The idea of supporting local people, even if they\'re in another country, is very appealing to us. We also talk about geographical indications, or GIs, which are a sign that a product is made from a specific geographical place.\n\nThis is a really important sign because it helps people know where the product came from, and it also helps people figure out who\'s using the product illegally. So, for example, if a company wants to use a product that\'s made in the U.S. to sell it in Africa, it has to have a sign saying that it came from Africa.',NULL,NULL),(69353,90,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Bridging The Social Distance - November 16, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-20 03:59:23','2023-11-16 19:06:35','In this episode, Jenny Mitchell, the host of the local community radio show Bridging the Social Distance, interviews Francois Daucourt, a long-term resident at Riverside Glen. The interview is recorded in 2023. Daucourt is a native of Verner, an area near the town of Surgeon Falls in northern Ontario.\n\nWhen he was young, he learned English at an English school in Welland. He also learned French at a French school in Verner. He says that the younger years were wild, like \"dancing and associating with my friends\" . However, when he turned 17 years old, he was \"boy crazy\" and had to learn to be careful with boys. His mother was strict with him, but he says that he thanks her for being so strict.','',NULL),(69354,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Democracy Now - November 16, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 08:02:04','2023-11-16 19:07:35','The war continues in the Gaza Strip, with dozens of Palestinians killed. Israel allows fuel to enter the Strip for the first time since the beginning of the conflict, but it does not allow it to be used for humanitarian purposes.\n\nAt the largest hospital, thousands of patients, doctors, and workers remain trapped inside, unable to move. The World Medical Association has condemned Israel\'s attack on the hospital, calling it an \"unacceptable military incursion into a hospital.\" The Israel Defense Forces have published images of weapons inside the hospital but have dismissed the images as propaganda. Vice President Joe Biden has also repeated Israeli claims that Hamas uses the hospital.',NULL,NULL),(69355,113,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Android’s Dungeon - November 16, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 13:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-18 12:49:49','2023-11-16 21:06:40',' The show is called \"Android\'s Dungeon,\" and it is hosted by Jack. He explains that it is now November and that the season is pre-holiday, meaning that people put up their Christmas decorations. ',NULL,NULL),(69356,13307,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Eclectic Selections - November 16, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 07:37:55','2023-11-16 21:07:47','Jack says that the show is a little too much like the Star Wars movies, but that it\'s got enough personality to keep it going. He also says that Mark Hamill is a talented actor and that he\'s playing a tough guy in the show. He says that it takes him a while to recognize him but that he does a good job of it. He hopes that next week he\'ll have some more content to talk about but until then, he says, he just wants to talk to his listeners.\n\nJack is on his way to Waterloo to see Rory Talion perform at Emmanuel United Church. He\'s going to start his show with some music from Metric and then he and Talion are going to sing some songs from the second season of the ABC show, \"The World According to Garp.\" The program ends with coffee and Mosna joins him to sing.',NULL,NULL),(69357,116,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/T.K.O. - November 16, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 07:24:05','2023-11-16 23:06:53','This is the second in a two-part interview with the co-host of the show, John, who is also known as \"Janan.\" He explains that the show is all about mixed martial arts and all about sports. He says that they are back in their studio at CFRU, and he\'s super excited to be there. He also says that the pandemic hit when he was recording the show at home, but it was better than anything. He thanks the listeners for their support and wishes he could do more sound bites in the show.',NULL,NULL),(69358,115,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/RadiOPIRG - November 16, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 15:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 07:14:33','2023-11-16 23:06:54','On this episode, the Host and his guest discuss a recent student walkout in Canada. The students walked out of school to protest against the silencing of Palestine\'s voices and to demand an end to Canadian complicity in the war crimes of the Israeli occupation. The Host also discusses the concept of resistance, which he believes is based on the idea that people are justified when they are occupied.',NULL,NULL),(69359,189,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/zrpkjf/VFTC_FallFR6n6v8.mp3','2023-11-17 00:16:04',288110758,'2023-11-17 07:02:10','2023-11-17 01:05:35','The show is called \"Vinyl From the Crypt,\" and it\'ll raise money for the community radio station. The show\'s host, Arcade Fire, is a big fan of Innitbound. He wants it to be the voice for the future of the city, and this is the place to help keep that voice strong.\n\nHe asks the listeners of the station to help him continue to give them all the great music spoken-word shows that they don\'t have anywhere else to listen to. He has a special guest who\'s here to pitch the idea and encourage people to support tonight: Melissa Rodway, the programming director of the alternative music station, the Bodway. She\'ll be giving a two-hour talk show, and the listeners can help by making a $100 donation to support the show tonight.',NULL,NULL),(69360,119,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Turtle Island Underground - November 16, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-20 04:14:44','2023-11-17 01:06:35','The first track is an instrumental called Spring Tide. The narrator says that this is spring and that breaking the ice is a chance for young people to participate in high stakes games. The next track is a spoken word piece called Ice Hopping. It was nominated for song of the year in the Native American music awards. The second track is another song that was nominated. This time it is a song by Washington Clean. Then there\'s a cover by Fleetwood Mac. The third track is one from Wot Legend. The fourth track is from Russell Wallace. The fifth track is also a cover of a song. The sixth track is some folksy music from G.',NULL,NULL