e explains that the latest round of violence between Israel and the Palestinians has been going on for a long time. He says that there is a growing international condemnation of Israel\'s treatment of the Palestinians, and the United Nations Security Council is close to passing a resolution for a humanitarian pause in the conflict. Israel has been running a trade surplus with the rest of the world, but the international community has started to isolate Israel.',NULL,NULL),(69453,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/21/Rainbow Country - November 21, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-21 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-21 07:27:00','2023-11-21 07:07:27','This is the first episode of a new program called \"Rainbow Country\" hosted by Carol Pope, author of \"Boy Erased\" and \"Memoirs\" and co-host of \"Gay Radio Show\" with Lorraine Segato and Mark Tara. The show is a daily hour-long show that focuses on Canadian films and is produced by Mark and hosted by Mark. In this show, Carol and her co-hosts discuss the films \"I Am Surat\" from Oscar nominated Deepa Mehta and \"Red Lights,\" a short film from the Toronto International Film festival. In addition, they discuss \"An Evening Out,\" a powerful indigenous feature.',NULL,NULL),(69454,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/21/Rainbow Country - November 21, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-21 01:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-21 09:25:41','2023-11-21 09:07:24','',NULL,NULL),(69455,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/21/CFRU Playlist - November 21, 2023 at 06:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-21 06:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-21 13:06:00','2023-11-21 13:06:00',NULL,NULL,NULL),(69456,207,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ka8ag4/Music_w_db_Hawkes_Nov_22_2023_podcastabc6r.mp3','2023-11-21 14:54:23',283265566,'2023-11-21 16:11:01','2023-11-21 15:05:46','The narrator and his wife are in their mid-forties and they\'re starting to get ready for the holidays. They\'re getting ready for Christmas meals, shopping,