'),(108,'Wind-Down','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Wind-Down-image.jpg','<p>a program that offers you a selection of musical vibes to help you drift into the night. Starts off with high energy beats that get progressively dreamier through the show.</p>','Serra Willow','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Wind-Down&posttype_search=mcm_recording','https://thewinddowncfru.blogspot.com/','',3600,'cfru-wind-down','en'),(109,'Radia','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Radia.jpg','<p>Radia is a network of independent radio stations, who have a common interest in promoting and producing artworks for the radio, and in forming related projects based on broadcasting and cultural exchange. Radia members produce a weekly radio show that is broadcast by each of the member radio stations. The shows represent the local artistic community of each station, whilst at the same time these new works point to an emergent collective notion of self-determined art for radio.</p>','Various','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Radia&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-radia','en'),(110,'Here Today','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Screen-Shot-2022-07-16-at-5.09.26-PM.jpeg','','Aaron Badgley','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Here%20Today&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-here-today','en'),(111,'Tales from the Bridge','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/TFTB-Header.jpg','<p>You can always find more Tales From The Bridge on Apple Podcasts our website, you can also find us on Twitter, Instagram, and Facebook to see what is happening on The Bridge.</p><p>Check out our many links!</p><p>Apple Podcasts:</p><p>#podcast #sciencefiction #scifi #scifipodcast #applepodcasts #soundtrack #cinematicsound #composer #starwars #imperialmarch</p>','Tristan, Marty, Kevin, and Sam','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Tales%20from%20the%20Bridge&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-tales-from-the-bridge','en'),(112,'FoodFarm Talk','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/FFT-For-CFRU.png','<p>FoodFarm Talk:</p><p>Food is life: We eat to live, and if there is anything worth celebrating, then it is food and the people behind it.</p><p>FoodFarm Talk is an interactive program that builds on the diversity of food research here at the University of Guelph and the strong agricultural and food community of the City of Guelph, to bring to listeners, among others, some of the wonderful works, being done from farm to fork. The program shows and celebrates the research, the people, and the activities that define the food we eat.</p>','Abdul-Rahim Abdulai, Emily Duncan, and Paul Smith','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=FoodFarm%20Talk&posttype_search=mcm_recording','https://anchor.fm/foodfarmtalk','',3600,'cfru-foodfarm-talk','en'),(113,'Android’s Dungeon','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/basement_stylised.jpg','<p>Enter the Android’s Dungeon with hosts Jack and Joel on a weekly show that discusses board and video games and their creators, the mechanics in them, and the culture around them. Give us a shout at androidsdungeon@cfru.ca or on twitter @ADRadioCFRU!</p>','Jack and Joel','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Android%26%238217%3Bs%20Dungeon&posttype_search=mcm_recording','https://twitter.com/ADRadioCFRU','androidsdungeon@cfru.ca',3600,'cfru-androids-dungeon','en'),(114,'Listen Up','cfru','','Show description coming soon!','Jack','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Listen%20Up&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-listen-up',NULL),(115,'RadiOPIRG','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/RadiOPIRG-1.png','<p>is our weekly spoken word show on CFRU 93.3FM, Guelph’s campus and community radio station, where we showcase the exciting work OPIRG is doing, and talk about current issues in the community related to social and environmental justice. Generally the show consists of recorded talks, live and pre-recorded interviews, spoken word pieces and music.  Listen to us on Thursdays from 3 to 4pm at 93.3FM.</p>','Omorowa Eguakun and Mandy Hiscocks','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=RadiOPIRG&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-radiopirg','en'),(116,'T.K.O.','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/T.K.O..jpg','<p>From analyzing fights to paying tribute to legendary athletes, T.K.O. keeps you updated on the hottest issues that surround the world of Mixed Martial Arts and combat sports. Beast mode is guaranteed!</p>','Janan','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=T.K.O.&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-t-k-o','en'),(117,'Café International','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Cafe-International-Take-Two.jpg','<p>Join host Dan Rosenberg on a radio series featuring interviews with musicians from around the world, from Fatoumata Diawara to Goran Bregović where we learn about folk music and its history.</p>','Daniel Rosenberg','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Caf%C3%A9%20International&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-cafe-international',NULL),(118,'Open Sources Guelph','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Open-Sources-Guelph.jpg','<p>Open Sources Guelph is a weekly news, politics and current events radio show on CFRU 93.3 FM, campus and community radio in Guelph. Picking up the baton passed down by the Beyond the Ballot Box and Gang of Four shows, Open Sources will remain a dedicated, informative and alternative media source in the Royal City. Our mission is to bring Guelph all the latest news, insight and interviews on both the big issues of the day, and the issues being overlooked by the mainstream media. You can listen to Open Sources live, every Thursday at 5 pm by tuning your radio 93.3 FM or you can listen to us online at cfru.ca. Open Sources Guelph is hosted and produced by Scotty Hertz McWhinnie (The Working Week) and Adam A. Donaldson (Guelph Politico).</p>','Scotty Hertz & Adam Donaldson','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Open%20Sources%20Guelph&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-open-sources-guelph','en'),(119,'Turtle Island Underground','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Turtle-Island-Underground-revised.png','','Mac','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Turtle%20Island%20Underground&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-turtle-island-underground','en'),(120,'The Crooked Beat','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/The-Crooked-Beat.jpg','<p>One of CFRU’s longest running and most beloved shows! Listen to Reggae, Dancehall, Ska & Rock Steady of all ages, styles and origins. “Don’t forget your history, know your destiny, In the abundance of water the fool is thirsty” (Bob Marley)</p>','Nicky Dread','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=The%20Crooked%20Beat&posttype_search=mcm_recording','http://nickydread.tripod.com/','nickydread@gmail.com',3600,'cfru-the-crooked-beat','en'),(121,'Sundowner','cfru','','<p>Finally, a show that brings the experience of staring out a bus window with headphones on to the airwaves. Tune in every other week for a selection of beloved gems, new releases, and left turns guaranteed to make today’s worries drift out of sight as you keep rolling.</p>','Matt Hollingshead','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Sundowner&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-sundowner','en'),(122,'Forever Deaf','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Dean-and-Todd-Forever-Deaf.jpg','<p>Dean and Todd have been on the air since 1987, and Forever Deaf has been in this format since 1989. Dean and Todd play all forms of extreme metal music, hardcore, punk, hard rock, and some prog for good measure.</p>','Dean and Todd','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Forever%20Deaf&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-forever-deaf','en'),(123,'Thanks for Listening :)','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Thanks-4-Listening.jpg','<p>Thanks For Listening</p>','Megan Arnold','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Thanks%20for%20Listening%20:%29&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-thanks-for-listening','en'),(124,'Planet Gr