fm',3600,'ciut-howl','en'),(181,'Reggae Riddims','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/CIUT-89.5FM.png','The best reggae you’ve ever heard.',' Patrick Roots','https://ciut.fm/shows/reggae-riddims/',NULL,'rasta@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-reggae-riddims','en'),(182,'No Beat Radio','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/20200512_080559-577x1024.jpg','Join Minesh Mandoda and No Beat Radio for a seamless journey through a world of unbound sound. Each show features both new and unknown ‘classics’ from Toronto and beyond that connect genres from electronica, folk, free jazz, garage, hip-hop, punk, krautrock and new world. From time to time a few guests and performances.',' Minesh Mandoda','https://ciut.fm/shows/no-beat-radio/','https://soundcloud.com/nobeatradio','nobeatradio@ciut.fm',3600,'ciut-no-beat-radio','en'),(183,'What Is Hip?','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Screenshot_20190105-142307_Facebook.jpg','Jazz, Latin-jazz, Jazz-Funk, Jazz-Fusion, SteelyDan. This is how the JazzFix rolls every week from 8 to 9pm. From 9 to 10pm - The lounge mix shifts gears into a DJ Set to round out the show.',' DjGoldfinger','https://ciut.fm/shows/what-is-hip/',NULL,'whatiship@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-what-is-hip',NULL),(184,'Six Degrees','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/image0.jpeg','Playing the best hidden gems and underground Hip-hop, Dub, Grime, Soul, R & B, from around the world. Includes interviews from local up-and-coming musicians and people behind the scenes. Chances are that your new favourite song was played here first.',' DJ SLAM! & Mlny','https://ciut.fm/shows/six-degrees/',NULL,'6degrees@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-six-degrees',NULL),(185,'A to Z Blues','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Screamin-Red-300x293.png','An introduction for many and an reintroduction for others to the forgotten blues artists in context with today’s performers.',' Screamin’ Red & Howlin\' Wolf Boy','https://ciut.fm/shows/a-to-z-blues/',NULL,'atozbluesonciut@gmail.com',3600,'ciut-a-to-z-blues','hi'),(186,'Higher Ground','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMGP1543-scaled.jpg','Funk, soul, and everything in between.',' Jason Palma','https://ciut.fm/shows/higher-ground/',NULL,NULL,7200,'ciut-higher-ground','en'),(187,'Dreaming In Stereo','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Dreaming-in-Stereo-scaled.jpg','This weekly show is hosted by Alexandra, U of T alumni and avid concertgoer. The music featured is a diverse mix of indie, rock, folk and electronic new releases. The focus is on uplifting local and international sounds and music news and announcements.',' Alexandra Simion','https://ciut.fm/shows/dreaming-in-stereo/','http://www.dreaminginstereo.ca/','dreaminginstereo@ciut.fm',3600,'ciut-dreaming-in-stereo','en'),(188,'Masterplan','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/MASTERPLAN_TMPS-LOGO-PNG-1024x1024.png','Celebrating over 30 years Hip Hop in your city and across Canada & U.S.A. worldwide. The Master Plan show started in 1989 with John Adams, Wendy Brathwaite aka Motion, Derrick aka Dj Power and Dave Clarke aka DJ DTS. The Masterplan show is run by the members of the community with volunteers from all across the city. DJ DTS is still on the show as a mentor for Generation Next founded by Dj Romeo aka Matthew Romeo and DTS, to give help and support to the younger generation who are interested in radio production, spoken word, Dj-ing, and life skills just to name a few. ','','https://ciut.fm/shows/masterplan/',NULL,NULL,7200,'ciut-masterplan','en'),(189,'Vinyl From the Crypt','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/20181012_150341.jpg','The Show for Audiophiles! For over a dozen years, Vinyl From The Crypt has given CIUT listeners and supporters the opportunity to come and present a 2-hour program featuring vinyl recordings from their personal collections.',' Sean Mitchell','https://ciut.fm/shows/vinyl-from-the-crypt/',NULL,'vinylfromthecrypt@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-vinyl-from-the-crypt','en'),(190,'The Bassment Sessions','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Dubmatix-CIUT.jpg','Bassment Sessions is a weekly music mix focusing on reggae, dub, funk, jungle, hip-hop and beyond. ',' Dubmatix','https://ciut.fm/shows/the-bassment-sessions/',NULL,NULL,3600,'ciut-the-bassment-sessions','en'),(191,'Frisson Radio','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Frission-Radio.jpg','Frisson has its origin as a French word, which translates to a thrill or shiver akin to goose bumps. Those pore raising feelings are the emotions we seek to evoke as we curate music & provide Canadian artists, producers and DJs with a platform for exposure and expression.',' Mikhael (Miks) Lamont & Nabeel Pervaiz','https://ciut.fm/shows/frisson-radio/',NULL,'frissonradio@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-frisson-radio',NULL),(192,'Veritable Infusion','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/300x300-0x000_4928554.jpg','VERITABLE INFUSION is one of several French translations for Naturally Flavoured. That is the only common denominator going on here; the music is naturally flavoured, crashing and gliding through many styles, from really old country and blues to dalliances with psychedelia, a lot of soul and funk from around the world, and usually topped off with a dose of reggae. Most weeks I insert some theme which is hoped to add some edification to the entertainment. Themes vary from the earliest Canadians to make American hits to the respective soul scenes of various countries, states and / or cities. An international music party going ‘All around the world for the funk’…',' DJ Erik T','https://ciut.fm/shows/veritable-infusion/','https://veritableinfusion.podomatic.com/','veritableinfusion@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-veritable-infusion',NULL),(193,'Classical Underground','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Philip-Conlon.png','Discover rare classical music gems and hear great stories too.',' Philip Conlon','https://ciut.fm/shows/classical-underground/',NULL,'classicalunderground@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-classical-underground','la'),(194,'Radio Boogie','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_0597-rotated.jpg','Radio Boogie focuses on today’s listener. Bluegrass and Old-Time music is today’s “folk” music, it is forever changing and forever relevant in today’s changing world of traditional musics.',' Steve Pritchard','https://ciut.fm/shows/radio-boogie/',NULL,'radioboogie@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-radio-boogie','en'),(195,'Dementia 13','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG-2150.jpg','Musical rarities from the other side of the Psychedelic Era. Early Prog Rock, Acid, Sunshine Pop, Garage, Beat, Freak Folk and Psychedelia of all sorts; the period’s best gems on 33-45 rpm.',' Christian Hamilton','https://ciut.fm/shows/dementia-13/','https://www.facebook.com/dementia13radio/','dementia13radio@gmail.com',7200,'ciut-dementia-13','en'),(196,'Across the Universe','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/91767915_10158588047969575_526689013419999232_o.jpg','A weekly musical and sonic journey connecting the pieces of an ever expanding mosaic of sound, interspersed with the delivery of small-chat of a human interest nature with some lyrical and mildly philosophical content.',' Ken Stowar','https://ciut.fm/shows/across-the-universe/',NULL,'acrosstheuniverse@ciut.fm',10800,'ciut-across-the-universe','en'),(197,'Phil’s Inn','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/ohio-phils-inn.jpg','Brad Reed has been involved in campus/community radio as on-air programmer since the 1970s. These past few years he has been honoured to be appointed General Manager/Custodian of Phil’s Inn. Drop in on Saturday afternoons, pull up a chair, sit by the fireplace, and take off your thirsty boots. Stay for awhile. Requests encouraged.',' Brad Reed','https://ciut.fm/shows/phils-inn/',NULL,NULL,7200,'ciut-phils-inn','en'),(198,'Ultra Latino','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/CIUT-Michelle-3330-sm.jpg','Tune in to Ultra Latino every Sunday from 2-3pm on CIUT 89.5 FM! We’re playing the best Latin music… new and old on your FM radio!',' Michelle (Dj Chelli)','https://ciut.fm/shows/ultra-latino/',NULL,'ultralatinoradio@gmail.com',3600,'ciut-ultra-latino',NULL),(199,'The Lovecast','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Lovecast-Banner-New-X-Flower-Cropped-for-CIUT-Page.png','Dave O Rama takes you on a journey through his schizophonic ears. From roots and blues to electronic moods, from orchestral to free form, dub stylistics, Latin soul psychedelics, global grooves, Afrocentric moves, and whatever other sonic delectables he digs up to stir into the pot.',' Dave O Rama','https://ciut.fm/shows/the-lovecast/',NULL,'lovecast@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-the-lovecast',NULL),(200,'Karibuni','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/thierno-and-nadine.jpg','A celebration of the cultures and music from the African continent.',' Nadine McNulty and Thierno Soumare','https://ciut.fm/shows/karibuni/',NULL,'karibuni@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-karibuni','en'),(201,'The More the Merrier','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/IMG_20230421_191011_660.jpg','donna g has been involved with CIUT 89.5 FM for almost 25 years. From being a member of the feminist collective \"By All Means\" in the 90\'s, to co-hosting the Caribbean-Filipino fusion show \"baba(eh) mama\" in the early 2000\'s to her present solo show, \"The More the Merrier.\" donna g has made it her goal to bring film, theatre and arts-at-large coverage to the broadest possible audience.',' donna g','https://ciut.fm/shows/the-more-the-merrier/',NULL,'tmtmwithdonnag@ciut.fm',3600,'ciut-the-more-the-merrier',NULL),(203,'The Bill King Show','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Bill-King-905x1024.jpg','New music, cultural waves, faces in the news, fresh ideas, a glimpse at the past, the sounds of the future – all done with humour, clarity and a determination to share the best in all of us.',' Bill King','https://ciut.fm/shows/the-bill-king-show/','https://www.mixcloud.com/6345789/the-bill-king-show-with-kim-stockwood-ciut-895-fm/','thebillkingshow@ciut.fm',3600,'ciut-the-bill-king-show',NULL),(204,'Meditation-Relaxation-Chill','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/newchill.jpg','Join us each Friday from 1- 3 pm for a mix of meditative, relaxing, and chill sounds and positive vibrations to help you through the remainder of your day.',NULL,'https://ciut.fm/shows/meditation-relaxation-chill/',NULL,'ken.stowar@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-meditation-relaxation-chill',NULL),(205,'Music At High Noon','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Music-at-High-Noon.png','Two hour open format music program. Genres include a variety of rock, surf, blues, jazz, funk, soul, and reggae.',' Mike Tadros','https://ciut.fm/shows/music-at-high-noon/',NULL,'highnoon@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-music-at-high-noon','en'),(206,'The Minx Sessions','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/40138933_10156334687820325_4252347171585654784_o.jpg','A musical appreciation show! Serving up new and old in abstract jazz, electronic, techno, deep house, soul, funk and anything to get you movin’!',' Binny the Minx','https://ciut.fm/shows/the-minx-sessions/','https://theminxsessions.com/','theminxsessions@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-the-minx-sessions','en'),(207,'Music With DB Hawkes','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/CIUT-89.5FM.png',NULL,' DB Hawkes','https://ciut.fm/shows/music-with-db-hawkes/',NULL,'dbhawkes@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-music-with-db-hawkes','en'),(209,'Turn Out Radio','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Turn-Out-Radio-Logo.jpg','Turn Out Radio is an innovative and engaging talk show which incorporates the latest in dance news within the national and international spectrum of current events. The broadcast platform connects with spotlighted guests to discover the heart of what moves us, and the latest in the news of our 