pen-minded discussion. We feature weekly interviews with international students, U of T professors, and local artists to learn more about the multicultural city of Toronto, Canada.',' Jesse McDougall','https://ciut.fm/shows/tracks-from-abroad/',NULL,'tracksfromabroad@ciut.fm',3600,'ciut-tracks-from-abroad','en'),(289,'The Next Stop','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Sage-CIUT.jpg','The Next Stop is the soundtrack to your night. Each episode follows a loose theme that draws from film scores and explores music from a wide range of genres and regions. We\'ll travel from 90\'s Boom-Bap to Space Age Pop to Tuareg Desert Blues to Peruvian Cumbia to 19th Century folk songs to celestial ambient tracks and everything in between for 2 hours every week.',' Sage Ranaldo','https://ciut.fm/shows/the-next-stop/',NULL,'thenextstop@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-the-next-stop','en'),(292,'The Cool Side of the Pillow','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/cool-side-of-the-pillow.png','Join us each Friday afternoon from 1-3 pm for The Cool Side of the Pillow . The program features a wide array of sound encompassing relaxing, chill, ambient, positive vibrations and much more all curated by Lydia. The program repeats on Sunday night at midnight until 2 am.',NULL,'https://ciut.fm/shows/the-cool-side-of-the-pillow/',NULL,'ken.stowar@ciut.fm',7200,'ciut-the-cool-side-of-the-pillow','en'),(296,'The Third Face','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/3rdface.jpg','The Third Face is commonly known as \"the face you hide from the world\" but this show is anything but an existential statement. The show is meant to bring new tracks to light that awaken the joy of discovering new music as an exciting hobby, or an hourly distraction!',' Victor Kovaleski','https://ciut.fm/shows/the-third-face/',NULL,'thethirdface@ciut.fm',3600,'ciut-the-third-face','en'),(1060,'Fridays at Five','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/a-dogs-breakfast-3.jpg','Discover emerging art and artists in Guelph while they showcase their personalities through interviews and games!','Amara Sheppard','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Fridays%20at%20Five&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,NULL,NULL),(1163,'Parallel Careers','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Parallel-Careers-Podcast-Image.jpg','<p>Parallel Careers is a show for creative writers—and the writers who teach them. The show features Canadian writers who are at the top of their game in both craft and pedagogy. Tune in to hear the big ideas and practical tips they take into their classrooms and their own craft.</p><p>Credits/team: Parallel Careers is produced by Claire Tacon, in partnership with The New Quarterly literary magazine. Erin MacIndoe Sproule is our Technical Producer and Story Editor. Music composed by Amadeo Ventura. Financial and in-kind support provided by the The Region of Waterloo Arts Fund, St. Jerome’s University, and the Government of Canada.</p>','','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Parallel%20Careers&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-parallel-careers',NULL),(1321,'Hong Kong Student Radio Association','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Hong-Kong-Student-Radio-Association.jpg','<p>Discussions, interviews and community news in Cantonese and English.</p>','Various','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Hong%20Kong%20Student%20Radio%20Association&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','hongkong@uoguelph.ca',3600,'cfru-hong-kong-student-radio-association','zh'),(1344,'Beautiful Druid','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/863F24D6-A669-47DB-9BD5-348BA141211A-1.jpeg','<p>Join host Alden Hadwen for a relaxed Sunday morning mix of music and poetry – for the day which we often set aside for pursuits close to our hearts. Whatever the activities you have planned, this program will give you a thoughtful start with some poetry to savour and some mellow music to set the tone – singer songwriters, jazz, classical and folk music tracks that you do not hear every day. This is a show for the garden of your mind; philosophical musings, letting your mind drift in the wind and the willows of beautiful music and words, all to go with a great cup of coffee and a slow easy start to the day.</p>','Alden Hadwen','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Beautiful%20Druid&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-beautiful-druid','en'),(1437,'Democracy Now','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/democracy-now.jpg','<p>With award-winning journalists Amy Goodman and Juan Gonzalez, Democracy Now is a national, daily, independent, award-winning news program airing on over 140 stations in North America.</p>','Amy Goodman','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Democracy%20Now&posttype_search=mcm_recording','http://www.democracynow.org/','',3600,'cfru-democracy-now','en'),(1438,'Worst Responders','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Worst-Responders-temporary-image.jpg','<p>Relationship troubles, work drama, or complicated life stuff that you just</p>','Renee and Charissa','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Worst%20Responders&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-worst-responders','en'),(1447,'Rainbow Country','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/CFRU-RC-BANNER-1.jpg','<p>Mark Tara is your guide through RAINBOW COUNTRY, a show that offers a blend of music & interviews giving voice to the LGBT community</p>','Mark Tara','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Rainbow%20Country&posttype_search=mcm_recording','http://www.marktara.com/','rainbowcountry@ciut.fm',3600,'cfru-rainbow-country','en'),(1451,'What Do You Know?','cfru','','<p>Long-form interviews!</p>','Gaon','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=What%20Do%20You%20Know%3F&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-what-do-you-know',NULL),(1453,'Silver Screen Dream Machine','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Silver-Screen-Dream-Machine.jpg','<p>Silver Screen Dream Machine is a collective approach to anything and everything to do with cinema, through interviewing people in and around the community who are involved with independent cinema, movie reviews and Bookshelf Cinema listings. We are always looking for contributors, so contact us if you are interested!</p>','Electrified Voltage and Boston Carlyle','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Silver%20Screen%20Dream%20Machine&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','silverscreen@cfru.ca',3600,'cfru-silver-screen-dream-machine','en'),(1455,'Down the Rabbit Hole','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/istockphoto-1302337885-612x612-1.jpeg','<p>Down the Rabbit Hole! Each week we’ll be looking at an artist and going down the rabbit hole of their musical journey! Whether this is through listening to their influences, checking out similar artists they’ve worked with, or exploring other musicians who may have been influenced themselves, the goal of this show is to showcase the million little threads that connect musicians in the industry!</p>','Hans Haryanto','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Down%20the%20Rabbit%20Hole&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-down-the-rabbit-hole','en'),(1464,'Gryphon And Special Olympics Sports Show','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Gryphon-And-Special-Olympics-Sports-Show.jpg','<p>There are sports to report, and Boston and Taylor have a boatload of things you’ve got to hear! It’s a free form celebration of sports and songs from all eras and styles, including hot new releases from local and Canadian artists. Don’t miss this dynamic team in action!</p>','Taylor and Boston Carlyle','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Gryphon%20And%20Special%20Olympics%20Sports%20Show&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','bostoncarlyle@gmail.com',3600,'cfru-gryphon-and-special-olympics-sports-show','en'),(1491,'Industry Tactics','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/industry-tactics.jpg','<p>Join Friendly Rich as he interviews some of the finest outsiders in Canadian music!</p>','Friendly Rich','https://www.cfru.ca/?s=Industry%20Tactics&posttype_search=mcm_recording','','',3600,'cfru-industry-tactics','en'),(1528,'Alternative Radio','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/David-Barsamian.jpg','Alternative Radio, established in 1986, is a weekly one-hour public affairs program offered free to all public radio stations in the US, Canada, Europe and beyond. AR provides information, analyses and views that are frequently ignored or distorted in other media.',' David Barsamian','https://ciut.fm/shows/alternative-radio/',NULL,NULL,3600,'ciut-alternative-radio',NULL),(1551,'Moovin\' In the Right Direction','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/IMG_0709-rotated.jpg','Heard every Thursday, the program features established and emerging talent both locally and internationally with a prime focus on independent Electronic music. Through guest DJ sets, artist interviews, event previews and reviews, emerging artists share the same platform with established ones creating a unique experience challenging the status quo in radio.',' David James','https://ciut.fm/shows/moovin-in-the-right-direction/',NULL,'moovinintherightdirection@ciut.fm',10800,'ciut-moovin-in-the-right-direction','en'),(1556,'The Green Majority','ciut','https://ciut.fm/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/tgm_hof.jpg','David Hostetter summarizes and combines news items and articles to create an audible admixture of elixirs and toxins. When not working on The Green Majority he is trying to convince Stefan to worship the sun and moon.',NULL,'https://ciut.fm/shows/the-green-majority/','http://www.greenmajority.ca/','greenmajority@ciut.fm',3600,'ciut-the-green-majority',NULL),(1586,'What Do You Do?','cfru','https://www.cfru.ca/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/What-Do-You-Do-Logo.png','<p>People all around us are unique. We each carry a hidden gem waiting to be uncovered by asking the right questions. So, on our show, we’ll be interviewing people of different career and educational paths to discover their unique experiences.</p>','Gaon','https://